WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:19.452 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.452 --> 00:00:20.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA MEREDITH:
Many of you have

00:00:20.910 --> 00:00:22.980 align:middle line:84%
seen the face of our
next guest, Mike Chen,

00:00:22.980 --> 00:00:25.170 align:middle line:90%
on YouTube on "Beyond Science."

00:00:25.170 --> 00:00:27.450 align:middle line:10%
He puts short but
succinct videos together

00:00:27.450 --> 00:00:30.360 align:middle line:10%
on scientific mysteries and
anomalies for a mass media

00:00:30.360 --> 00:00:32.640 align:middle line:10%
audience who is very
curious but oftentimes

00:00:32.640 --> 00:00:33.990 align:middle line:10%
new to these subjects.

00:00:33.990 --> 00:00:36.890 align:middle line:84%
His story is a unique one
as he was raised in China,

00:00:36.890 --> 00:00:39.135 align:middle line:84%
and he's a practitioner
of a form of qigong

00:00:39.135 --> 00:00:41.010 align:middle line:84%
that is banned by the
government there, which

00:00:41.010 --> 00:00:42.480 align:middle line:90%
means he can't really go home.

00:00:42.480 --> 00:00:45.860 align:middle line:84%
But he's certainly making
the best of life in America.

00:00:45.860 --> 00:00:46.660 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Mike.

00:00:46.660 --> 00:00:47.250 align:middle line:90%
It's wonderful.

00:00:47.250 --> 00:00:49.000 align:middle line:84%
We've been chatting
off camera, and you're

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:52.740 align:middle line:84%
just absolutely delightful,
just a really open hearted, open

00:00:52.740 --> 00:00:54.960 align:middle line:84%
spirited person, which
is I think why you

00:00:54.960 --> 00:00:56.220 align:middle line:90%
have gajillions of followers.

00:00:56.220 --> 00:00:58.345 align:middle line:84%
>>MIKE CHEN: Well, thank
you so much for having me.

00:00:58.345 --> 00:01:01.200 align:middle line:10%
It's such a pleasure to meet
you and be here talking to you.

00:01:01.200 --> 00:01:02.290 align:middle line:90%
And thank you so much.

00:01:02.290 --> 00:01:03.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:01:03.090 --> 00:01:04.980 align:middle line:84%
And I want to start
getting into your story

00:01:04.980 --> 00:01:07.230 align:middle line:84%
because it's not one that most
people here are familiar with.

00:01:07.230 --> 00:01:08.096 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Sure.

00:01:08.096 --> 00:01:11.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And we're going to be
talking a little bit about this

00:01:11.100 --> 00:01:13.270 align:middle line:90%
form of qigong that is so--

00:01:13.270 --> 00:01:14.380 align:middle line:90%
and find out why it's so--

00:01:14.380 --> 00:01:15.180 align:middle line:90%
how powerful it is.

00:01:15.180 --> 00:01:15.590 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Right.

00:01:15.590 --> 00:01:17.280 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What we
can do with it by way

00:01:17.280 --> 00:01:20.340 align:middle line:84%
of our own personal expansion
if we access to learning it

00:01:20.340 --> 00:01:22.290 align:middle line:84%
and also why the
Chinese government is so

00:01:22.290 --> 00:01:22.830 align:middle line:90%
threatened by it.

00:01:22.830 --> 00:01:25.260 align:middle line:84%
And there is-- I will give
everyone a heads up right now--

00:01:25.260 --> 00:01:28.650 align:middle line:84%
there's a little bit of a dark
thread in this story, which

00:01:28.650 --> 00:01:30.700 align:middle line:84%
is important for people
to know about as well,

00:01:30.700 --> 00:01:32.560 align:middle line:84%
but we're not going to hang
out in that area too long.

00:01:32.560 --> 00:01:33.417 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yeah.

00:01:33.417 --> 00:01:34.875 align:middle line:84%
There's a sad, very
sad part of it.

00:01:34.875 --> 00:01:35.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Very sad.

00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:36.610 align:middle line:90%
And we'll get to that in a bit.

00:01:36.610 --> 00:01:38.530 align:middle line:84%
And then I'm hoping
we have some time left

00:01:38.530 --> 00:01:39.655 align:middle line:90%
because we're both foodies.

00:01:39.655 --> 00:01:40.146 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Of course.

00:01:40.146 --> 00:01:42.521 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And we're going to
talk about dumplings and dim

00:01:42.521 --> 00:01:43.325 align:middle line:90%
sum.

00:01:43.325 --> 00:01:45.210 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: That's what-- that's
what they used to call me

00:01:45.210 --> 00:01:46.293 align:middle line:90%
in high school, Dumplings.

00:01:46.293 --> 00:01:48.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: [LAUGHS] Dumplings!

00:01:48.060 --> 00:01:49.560 align:middle line:90%
Yes, I love it.

00:01:49.560 --> 00:01:52.195 align:middle line:84%
So let's start out with you
as a little kid in China,

00:01:52.195 --> 00:01:53.820 align:middle line:84%
what your life was
like, and I know you

00:01:53.820 --> 00:01:55.300 align:middle line:90%
had an accident at a young age.

00:01:55.300 --> 00:01:56.800 align:middle line:84%
So let's-- start
telling your story.

00:01:56.800 --> 00:01:57.000 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Sure.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:57.800 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yeah.

00:01:57.800 --> 00:01:59.020 align:middle line:90%
So I grew up in China.

00:01:59.020 --> 00:02:01.050 align:middle line:84%
Well, I grew up 'til the
age of eight in China,

00:02:01.050 --> 00:02:05.310 align:middle line:84%
and I was born in the old
capital, which is called Xi'an.

00:02:05.310 --> 00:02:07.660 align:middle line:10%
So this is the original
capital of China.

00:02:07.660 --> 00:02:10.740 align:middle line:10%
When China was
formed to its first--

00:02:10.740 --> 00:02:12.942 align:middle line:10%
as a country, this
was the capital.

00:02:12.942 --> 00:02:14.650 align:middle line:84%
And not a lot of people
used to go there.

00:02:14.650 --> 00:02:17.070 align:middle line:84%
It's considered a
poorer part of China,

00:02:17.070 --> 00:02:21.450 align:middle line:84%
but I consider it the
best foods in China

00:02:21.450 --> 00:02:23.323 align:middle line:90%
you can find is in my city.

00:02:23.323 --> 00:02:24.990 align:middle line:84%
People say that, but
I actually mean it.

00:02:24.990 --> 00:02:25.993 align:middle line:90%
I think it's 100% true.

00:02:25.993 --> 00:02:27.660 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I think
almost-- no one's even

00:02:27.660 --> 00:02:29.130 align:middle line:90%
heard of this city in the West.

00:02:29.130 --> 00:02:29.930 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: No, no.

00:02:29.930 --> 00:02:31.690 align:middle line:84%
It's very-- it's--
because the food--

00:02:31.690 --> 00:02:35.490 align:middle line:84%
people have heard of Cantonese
food or Szechuan food,

00:02:35.490 --> 00:02:39.660 align:middle line:84%
and they relate that to
a province back in China.

00:02:39.660 --> 00:02:41.970 align:middle line:84%
But Xi'an food is
not as popular here.

00:02:41.970 --> 00:02:43.397 align:middle line:90%
But again like I said it's--

00:02:43.397 --> 00:02:44.480 align:middle line:90%
I feel like it's the best.

00:02:44.480 --> 00:02:44.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:02:44.730 --> 00:02:46.140 align:middle line:84%
Let's just talk food
just for a minute.

00:02:46.140 --> 00:02:46.332 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: OK.

00:02:46.332 --> 00:02:46.430 align:middle line:90%
Sure.

00:02:46.430 --> 00:02:48.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So OK, what's the
characteristic as compared

00:02:48.900 --> 00:02:51.320 align:middle line:90%
to Cantonese and Szechuan?

00:02:51.320 --> 00:02:52.170 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Szechuan.

00:02:52.170 --> 00:02:54.420 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's many different
types cuisine in China.

00:02:54.420 --> 00:02:57.060 align:middle line:84%
And in the north, we eat a
lot more noodles and buns,

00:02:57.060 --> 00:02:59.117 align:middle line:84%
basically a lot
more wheat items.

00:02:59.117 --> 00:02:59.950 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Dumplings.

00:02:59.950 --> 00:03:02.870 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: Yeah, because we don't
grow rice that well up north.

00:03:02.870 --> 00:03:05.310 align:middle line:84%
So Xi'an food is
a lot of noodles,

00:03:05.310 --> 00:03:10.200 align:middle line:84%
a lot of buns, like pork
buns, and grilled buns,

00:03:10.200 --> 00:03:13.530 align:middle line:84%
and fried buns, and all sorts
of buns is from the north.

00:03:13.530 --> 00:03:16.350 align:middle line:84%
And that's what our
city does the best is

00:03:16.350 --> 00:03:18.360 align:middle line:90%
buns and noodles and dumplings.

00:03:18.360 --> 00:03:20.330 align:middle line:90%
And that's what we're known for.

00:03:20.330 --> 00:03:21.780 align:middle line:90%
And it's delicious.

00:03:21.780 --> 00:03:22.870 align:middle line:90%
It's the best.

00:03:22.870 --> 00:03:23.670 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:03:23.670 --> 00:03:24.960 align:middle line:84%
So you've got a
plug in for that.

00:03:24.960 --> 00:03:25.500 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yes.

00:03:25.500 --> 00:03:26.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You have
a show on food, too.

00:03:26.890 --> 00:03:27.190 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: I do.

00:03:27.190 --> 00:03:27.390 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:03:27.390 --> 00:03:28.800 align:middle line:90%
I do have a food show.

00:03:28.800 --> 00:03:29.637 align:middle line:90%
I'm a huge foodie.

00:03:29.637 --> 00:03:30.970 align:middle line:90%
So there's two loves in my life.

00:03:30.970 --> 00:03:34.800 align:middle line:84%
I love exploring the unknown,
the mysteries in the universe.

00:03:34.800 --> 00:03:36.120 align:middle line:90%
And I love to eat.

00:03:36.120 --> 00:03:38.850 align:middle line:84%
Because, hey, when you get tired
of exploring the mysteries,

00:03:38.850 --> 00:03:39.750 align:middle line:90%
you got to chow down.

00:03:39.750 --> 00:03:41.610 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so you're my
soul brother, because that's

00:03:41.610 --> 00:03:42.410 align:middle line:90%
the same with me.

00:03:42.410 --> 00:03:43.440 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: That's awesome.

00:03:43.440 --> 00:03:45.482 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I go to the
kitchen and start baking it

00:03:45.482 --> 00:03:46.740 align:middle line:90%
for the other half of my life.

00:03:46.740 --> 00:03:47.040 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:03:47.040 --> 00:03:48.360 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about
your life in China.

00:03:48.360 --> 00:03:49.160 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: OK.

00:03:49.160 --> 00:03:51.450 align:middle line:90%
So I grew up in Xi'an.

00:03:51.450 --> 00:03:54.300 align:middle line:84%
My parents-- my dad was
a professor and my mom

00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:56.100 align:middle line:90%
was in the government.

00:03:56.100 --> 00:03:58.560 align:middle line:84%
And we grew up in
government housing.

00:03:58.560 --> 00:04:01.560 align:middle line:84%
Back then, most housing actually
kind of looked very similar

00:04:01.560 --> 00:04:03.100 align:middle line:90%
to each other.

00:04:03.100 --> 00:04:05.160 align:middle line:84%
So I was there
till second grade,

00:04:05.160 --> 00:04:06.690 align:middle line:84%
eight-years old,
and I moved here.

00:04:06.690 --> 00:04:09.300 align:middle line:90%
But I started--

00:04:09.300 --> 00:04:10.230 align:middle line:90%
I don't know why.

00:04:10.230 --> 00:04:15.030 align:middle line:84%
Thinking back, I think
my love for the mysteries

00:04:15.030 --> 00:04:17.763 align:middle line:84%
of the universe and
why we're all here,

00:04:17.763 --> 00:04:19.930 align:middle line:84%
I started thinking about
that at a really young age.

00:04:19.930 --> 00:04:22.050 align:middle line:84%
I remember-- back
when you're a kid,

00:04:22.050 --> 00:04:24.690 align:middle line:84%
you talk about, oh, maybe
there's monsters in the world.

00:04:24.690 --> 00:04:25.770 align:middle line:90%
Maybe there's ghosts.

00:04:25.770 --> 00:04:28.440 align:middle line:84%
Maybe this place is haunted
place, that place is haunted.

00:04:28.440 --> 00:04:30.110 align:middle line:90%
I was so into that.

00:04:30.110 --> 00:04:33.990 align:middle line:84%
And one specific
incident that happened

00:04:33.990 --> 00:04:37.410 align:middle line:84%
when I was a kid that
I remember clearly,

00:04:37.410 --> 00:04:43.830 align:middle line:84%
it changed the way I
think I perceive what

00:04:43.830 --> 00:04:46.650 align:middle line:84%
the purpose of life
is and kind of like

00:04:46.650 --> 00:04:49.470 align:middle line:84%
made me question
everything even more.

00:04:49.470 --> 00:04:52.860 align:middle line:84%
Because what happened
to me was pretty insane.

00:04:52.860 --> 00:04:55.170 align:middle line:84%
I was-- me and a
bunch of friends

00:04:55.170 --> 00:04:57.360 align:middle line:84%
were playing outside our
apartment complex, which

00:04:57.360 --> 00:05:00.570 align:middle line:84%
was near this little
bit of a highway, cars

00:05:00.570 --> 00:05:01.380 align:middle line:90%
going pretty fast.

00:05:01.380 --> 00:05:04.740 align:middle line:84%
And we were running
from a bully.

00:05:04.740 --> 00:05:05.770 align:middle line:90%
And he was chasing us.

00:05:05.770 --> 00:05:06.570 align:middle line:90%
He saw us.

00:05:06.570 --> 00:05:07.140 align:middle line:90%
He came over.

00:05:07.140 --> 00:05:09.030 align:middle line:84%
I mean, Chinese kids,
like, you see each other,

00:05:09.030 --> 00:05:09.690 align:middle line:90%
you beat each other up.

00:05:09.690 --> 00:05:09.970 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:05:09.970 --> 00:05:11.520 align:middle line:84%
That's how we greet
each other back then.

00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:12.930 align:middle line:90%
So I didn't want to get beat up.

00:05:12.930 --> 00:05:13.920 align:middle line:90%
And he's chasing us.

00:05:13.920 --> 00:05:17.430 align:middle line:84%
I remember still, very vividly
to this day, me and my friends,

00:05:17.430 --> 00:05:19.230 align:middle line:84%
we decided to run
across the street,

00:05:19.230 --> 00:05:21.840 align:middle line:84%
because we figured he wouldn't
dare follow us across street

00:05:21.840 --> 00:05:23.252 align:middle line:90%
because so many cars coming.

00:05:23.252 --> 00:05:24.210 align:middle line:90%
So we didn't even look.

00:05:24.210 --> 00:05:25.480 align:middle line:84%
And we just dashed
across the street.

00:05:25.480 --> 00:05:26.640 align:middle line:90%
It was kind of dusk now.

00:05:26.640 --> 00:05:28.300 align:middle line:90%
It was like not so bright.

00:05:28.300 --> 00:05:31.560 align:middle line:84%
And again, it's not so
bright for me to do that.

00:05:31.560 --> 00:05:32.360 align:middle line:90%
And we made it.

00:05:32.360 --> 00:05:35.520 align:middle line:84%
And then the bully ran after
us, and then he made it, too.

00:05:35.520 --> 00:05:37.260 align:middle line:84%
And then, we're like,
OK, let's run back.

00:05:37.260 --> 00:05:38.700 align:middle line:90%
So my friend ran back.

00:05:38.700 --> 00:05:40.680 align:middle line:90%
And I-- I remember hesitating.

00:05:40.680 --> 00:05:44.110 align:middle line:84%
I remember I ran to the middle
of the street, and I hesitated.

00:05:44.110 --> 00:05:45.690 align:middle line:84%
In that one second
of hesitation,

00:05:45.690 --> 00:05:47.290 align:middle line:90%
I felt something hit me--

00:05:47.290 --> 00:05:48.090 align:middle line:90%
smack.

00:05:48.090 --> 00:05:49.920 align:middle line:84%
And I felt myself
flying in the air.

00:05:49.920 --> 00:05:51.080 align:middle line:90%
And I could see--

00:05:51.080 --> 00:05:53.360 align:middle line:90%
not like flying out of my body.

00:05:53.360 --> 00:05:55.433 align:middle line:84%
I could feel my body
flying in the air.

00:05:55.433 --> 00:05:57.600 align:middle line:84%
And I could see my friend
who ran across the street,

00:05:57.600 --> 00:05:59.652 align:middle line:90%
and he was laughing.

00:05:59.652 --> 00:06:00.610 align:middle line:90%
Not such a good friend.

00:06:00.610 --> 00:06:01.014 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Laughing?

00:06:01.014 --> 00:06:02.088 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: He was laugh--

00:06:02.088 --> 00:06:03.380 align:middle line:90%
What kind of person laughs at--

00:06:03.380 --> 00:06:06.000 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: When your
friend's been hit by a car.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:07.710 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: So anyway,
because you're a kid,

00:06:07.710 --> 00:06:10.420 align:middle line:90%
you go, oh, he's laughing.

00:06:10.420 --> 00:06:13.470 align:middle line:84%
And I remember up in the
sky just, I'm like, oh.

00:06:13.470 --> 00:06:15.450 align:middle line:90%
And then I hit the ground hard.

00:06:15.450 --> 00:06:16.320 align:middle line:90%
And I bounced.

00:06:16.320 --> 00:06:19.380 align:middle line:84%
And I remember just like
bouncing on the ground.

00:06:19.380 --> 00:06:20.970 align:middle line:90%
And then everything stops.

00:06:20.970 --> 00:06:23.360 align:middle line:84%
And then the next thing I
know, the driver came out.

00:06:23.360 --> 00:06:24.490 align:middle line:90%
It was a truck.

00:06:24.490 --> 00:06:25.740 align:middle line:90%
And the truck driver came out.

00:06:25.740 --> 00:06:26.770 align:middle line:90%
He was like, are you OK?

00:06:26.770 --> 00:06:27.510 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, yeah, yeah.

00:06:27.510 --> 00:06:27.960 align:middle line:90%
I'm fine.

00:06:27.960 --> 00:06:28.760 align:middle line:90%
I'm fine.

00:06:28.760 --> 00:06:30.590 align:middle line:84%
And back then, I didn't
want any trouble.

00:06:30.590 --> 00:06:32.548 align:middle line:84%
And that's kind of our
mentality back then was,

00:06:32.548 --> 00:06:33.570 align:middle line:90%
don't get in trouble.

00:06:33.570 --> 00:06:36.325 align:middle line:84%
You know, just if you're
OK, just come home.

00:06:36.325 --> 00:06:37.450 align:middle line:90%
So I was telling everybody.

00:06:37.450 --> 00:06:39.370 align:middle line:84%
And by this time, the
entire road has stopped.

00:06:39.370 --> 00:06:40.870 align:middle line:84%
I remember all the
drivers came out,

00:06:40.870 --> 00:06:43.410 align:middle line:84%
because it was a
fairly big thing.

00:06:43.410 --> 00:06:45.550 align:middle line:84%
And then I just said,
no, no, no, I'm fine.

00:06:45.550 --> 00:06:46.350 align:middle line:90%
Look at me.

00:06:46.350 --> 00:06:47.370 align:middle line:90%
I don't have--

00:06:47.370 --> 00:06:48.660 align:middle line:90%
I'm not broken or anything.

00:06:48.660 --> 00:06:49.650 align:middle line:90%
Let me go home.

00:06:49.650 --> 00:06:52.410 align:middle line:84%
And finally, he was, OK, if
you're sure, then go home.

00:06:52.410 --> 00:06:55.170 align:middle line:84%
So I ran home with my
friend, and I even asked him.

00:06:55.170 --> 00:06:56.650 align:middle line:90%
I said, why were you laughing?

00:06:56.650 --> 00:06:59.317 align:middle line:84%
And he was like, well, because
you flew so high in the air.

00:06:59.317 --> 00:07:00.150 align:middle line:90%
That's what he said.

00:07:00.150 --> 00:07:01.600 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you
were struck hard?

00:07:01.600 --> 00:07:02.850 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Oh, I was struck hard.

00:07:02.850 --> 00:07:04.450 align:middle line:90%
And then I went home.

00:07:04.450 --> 00:07:06.150 align:middle line:90%
And nothing happened.

00:07:06.150 --> 00:07:10.130 align:middle line:84%
And I ate dinner,
and I was in bed.

00:07:10.130 --> 00:07:13.680 align:middle line:84%
And after that, thinking
about it, it freaked me out.

00:07:13.680 --> 00:07:14.800 align:middle line:90%
And then I started crying.

00:07:14.800 --> 00:07:17.230 align:middle line:84%
Then, I was like, Mom,
I got hit by a car.

00:07:17.230 --> 00:07:18.910 align:middle line:84%
And then my mom
started freaking out,

00:07:18.910 --> 00:07:22.050 align:middle line:84%
and she takes me to the
hospital right away that night.

00:07:22.050 --> 00:07:24.260 align:middle line:90%
Not a scratch on me.

00:07:24.260 --> 00:07:25.060 align:middle line:90%
And I was like--

00:07:25.060 --> 00:07:26.435 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Were
you-- no bruises--

00:07:26.435 --> 00:07:27.235 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Nothing.

00:07:27.235 --> 00:07:28.410 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Or impacts at all?

00:07:28.410 --> 00:07:29.368 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Nothing at all.

00:07:29.368 --> 00:07:31.200 align:middle line:84%
Doctors were like,
there's really nothing.

00:07:31.200 --> 00:07:32.160 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing.

00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:34.420 align:middle line:84%
So at the time, I
was like, all right.

00:07:34.420 --> 00:07:35.220 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:07:35.220 --> 00:07:36.798 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what this means.

00:07:36.798 --> 00:07:39.090 align:middle line:84%
But later in life when I'm
thinking about this, I mean,

00:07:39.090 --> 00:07:40.600 align:middle line:90%
this is really impossible.

00:07:40.600 --> 00:07:41.400 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:07:41.400 --> 00:07:42.930 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: How did
this even happen?

00:07:42.930 --> 00:07:46.115 align:middle line:84%
So I started thinking,
OK, maybe, I don't know.

00:07:46.115 --> 00:07:48.240 align:middle line:84%
Maybe there's something
I'm supposed to do in life,

00:07:48.240 --> 00:07:50.160 align:middle line:84%
like maybe I'm
here for a reason.

00:07:50.160 --> 00:07:54.420 align:middle line:84%
There must be something more
than OK, live your life,

00:07:54.420 --> 00:07:55.700 align:middle line:90%
get married, have kids, die.

00:07:55.700 --> 00:07:59.760 align:middle line:84%
Like there must be something
more to it than that.

00:07:59.760 --> 00:08:03.100 align:middle line:84%
And that's what got me propelled
into thinking, let's dive

00:08:03.100 --> 00:08:03.900 align:middle line:90%
into this more.

00:08:03.900 --> 00:08:07.390 align:middle line:84%
Let's see what other cases of
these there are in the world.

00:08:07.390 --> 00:08:10.060 align:middle line:84%
Let's see what other
strange phenomenon questions

00:08:10.060 --> 00:08:10.860 align:middle line:90%
people have.

00:08:10.860 --> 00:08:13.530 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I became really
interested in all this stuff

00:08:13.530 --> 00:08:15.940 align:middle line:90%
after I came to America.

00:08:15.940 --> 00:08:16.740 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:08:16.740 --> 00:08:17.580 align:middle line:90%
Interesting.

00:08:17.580 --> 00:08:22.290 align:middle line:84%
Well, As you've looked back
on it, on that event that day,

00:08:22.290 --> 00:08:24.930 align:middle line:90%
what have you come to?

00:08:24.930 --> 00:08:31.310 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: I do think, 100%, that
that was not just a simple

00:08:31.310 --> 00:08:32.500 align:middle line:90%
get hit by a truck.

00:08:32.500 --> 00:08:34.210 align:middle line:84%
And I don't believe
in coincidences.

00:08:34.210 --> 00:08:35.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:08:35.010 --> 00:08:35.968 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: I really don't.

00:08:35.968 --> 00:08:40.260 align:middle line:84%
I don't feel like anything
in life is a coincidence.

00:08:40.260 --> 00:08:43.559 align:middle line:84%
I feel everything is-- in
Chinese, we call it [CHINESE],,

00:08:43.559 --> 00:08:46.830 align:middle line:84%
which means like a
interpersonal, karmic

00:08:46.830 --> 00:08:49.890 align:middle line:84%
relationship we have
with everyone around us.

00:08:49.890 --> 00:08:53.250 align:middle line:84%
People we meet on a daily
basis even for a second,

00:08:53.250 --> 00:08:55.920 align:middle line:84%
there is a certain
amount of [CHINESE]..

00:08:55.920 --> 00:08:57.200 align:middle line:90%
That's the reason why we met.

00:08:57.200 --> 00:09:04.690 align:middle line:84%
There's an old Chinese
saying, called [CHINESE],,

00:09:04.690 --> 00:09:07.500 align:middle line:84%
which means 10 years
of karmic relationship

00:09:07.500 --> 00:09:09.350 align:middle line:84%
will get you on the
same boat together

00:09:09.350 --> 00:09:11.190 align:middle line:84%
and a hundred years
of karmic relationship

00:09:11.190 --> 00:09:13.680 align:middle line:90%
will get you married together.

00:09:13.680 --> 00:09:16.860 align:middle line:84%
So Chinese are-- we
consider this almost--

00:09:16.860 --> 00:09:20.055 align:middle line:84%
this is part of our culture,
like the traditional culture.

00:09:20.055 --> 00:09:22.180 align:middle line:84%
Now, there's not so much
for modern Chinese people.

00:09:22.180 --> 00:09:23.973 align:middle line:84%
But traditional culture,
like in history,

00:09:23.973 --> 00:09:25.140 align:middle line:90%
that's what people believed.

00:09:25.140 --> 00:09:27.060 align:middle line:90%
And I believed in that as well.

00:09:27.060 --> 00:09:29.910 align:middle line:84%
And thinking back, I do
feel like I was here.

00:09:29.910 --> 00:09:32.320 align:middle line:84%
There's a purpose
for me being here.

00:09:32.320 --> 00:09:35.080 align:middle line:90%
And I think I figured that out.

00:09:35.080 --> 00:09:40.865 align:middle line:84%
But I do not think it was just
so I could just live a life

00:09:40.865 --> 00:09:41.740 align:middle line:90%
and grow old and die.

00:09:41.740 --> 00:09:42.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:09:42.100 --> 00:09:42.635 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:09:42.635 --> 00:09:44.970 align:middle line:84%
And so do you feel that there
was some kind of protection,

00:09:44.970 --> 00:09:46.830 align:middle line:84%
there was something
that happened that day--

00:09:46.830 --> 00:09:47.240 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: For sure, yeah.

00:09:47.240 --> 00:09:49.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --that allowed
you to remain unscathed so

00:09:49.470 --> 00:09:51.960 align:middle line:84%
that you can reflect on it
later and say, I have purpose?

00:09:51.960 --> 00:09:52.260 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yes.

00:09:52.260 --> 00:09:53.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:09:53.060 --> 00:09:56.910 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: I mean, I think, at
least for me I believe there

00:09:56.910 --> 00:10:00.105 align:middle line:84%
are so many things in the world
that we cannot see or touch.

00:10:00.105 --> 00:10:02.730 align:middle line:84%
I mean, scientifically speaking,
there are many of those things

00:10:02.730 --> 00:10:03.990 align:middle line:90%
already, like radio waves.

00:10:03.990 --> 00:10:06.970 align:middle line:84%
And you can't see anything,
but they're there.

00:10:06.970 --> 00:10:09.030 align:middle line:84%
I do believe that
there are things

00:10:09.030 --> 00:10:13.650 align:middle line:84%
out there that you could say,
they're watching out for you,

00:10:13.650 --> 00:10:18.720 align:middle line:84%
or intervening because
of some bigger purpose.

00:10:18.720 --> 00:10:20.520 align:middle line:84%
But I believe there
are those entities.

00:10:20.520 --> 00:10:22.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It. certainly
seems to fit that category.

00:10:22.350 --> 00:10:22.830 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: I think so.

00:10:22.830 --> 00:10:23.913 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So here you are.

00:10:23.913 --> 00:10:26.940 align:middle line:84%
A couple of years later, you
end up in the United States.

00:10:26.940 --> 00:10:28.000 align:middle line:90%
How did that happen?

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:30.660 align:middle line:84%
How did your parents end up
coming to the United States?

00:10:30.660 --> 00:10:33.540 align:middle line:10%
>>CHEN: It's kind of crazy,
because technically, we

00:10:33.540 --> 00:10:37.270 align:middle line:10%
shouldn't have because my
mom had a great job in China.

00:10:37.270 --> 00:10:38.520 align:middle line:10%
She was a government official.

00:10:38.520 --> 00:10:40.145 align:middle line:84%
She could have been
a bigger government

00:10:40.145 --> 00:10:41.350 align:middle line:90%
official as time moved on.

00:10:41.350 --> 00:10:43.290 align:middle line:84%
And of course, we
know now if you're

00:10:43.290 --> 00:10:45.650 align:middle line:84%
a major official in China,
you're going to be rich.

00:10:45.650 --> 00:10:49.390 align:middle line:84%
You're going to
have a great life.

00:10:49.390 --> 00:10:52.110 align:middle line:84%
But my parents were only
in the US-- they only

00:10:52.110 --> 00:10:54.450 align:middle line:84%
wanted to come for a
year to kind of see what

00:10:54.450 --> 00:10:55.680 align:middle line:90%
it is and see what it's like.

00:10:55.680 --> 00:10:59.110 align:middle line:84%
And then they stay because
they said I wanted to stay.

00:10:59.110 --> 00:11:00.567 align:middle line:90%
And that's why they stayed.

00:11:00.567 --> 00:11:01.650 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, interesting.

00:11:01.650 --> 00:11:02.200 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: That's what they say.

00:11:02.200 --> 00:11:02.311 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So you drove that.

00:11:02.311 --> 00:11:03.090 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: I don't remember that.

00:11:03.090 --> 00:11:04.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, but--
so you drove that.

00:11:04.620 --> 00:11:06.210 align:middle line:84%
And did you have
brothers or sisters?

00:11:06.210 --> 00:11:07.010 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: No.

00:11:07.010 --> 00:11:09.000 align:middle line:84%
So you were the baby
that had already

00:11:09.000 --> 00:11:10.590 align:middle line:90%
gone through this experience.

00:11:10.590 --> 00:11:14.940 align:middle line:84%
And obviously, because you
have a very unique spark,

00:11:14.940 --> 00:11:16.983 align:middle line:84%
you know, spark and
intention in you,

00:11:16.983 --> 00:11:18.900 align:middle line:84%
that is that je ne sais
quoi, which is why you

00:11:18.900 --> 00:11:19.890 align:middle line:90%
have gajillions of followers--

00:11:19.890 --> 00:11:20.350 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Oh, thank you.

00:11:20.350 --> 00:11:20.630 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much.

00:11:20.630 --> 00:11:21.660 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because
it is who you are.

00:11:21.660 --> 00:11:22.785 align:middle line:90%
That spirit shines through.

00:11:22.785 --> 00:11:26.160 align:middle line:84%
And so obviously raising you,
they felt and saw that spirit.

00:11:26.160 --> 00:11:30.240 align:middle line:84%
And so it sounds like they
chose to foster it, if not let

00:11:30.240 --> 00:11:32.070 align:middle line:84%
it be a guide even
in their own lives.

00:11:32.070 --> 00:11:33.960 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yeah, I mean.

00:11:33.960 --> 00:11:34.800 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much.

00:11:34.800 --> 00:11:35.600 align:middle line:90%
That's very kind.

00:11:35.600 --> 00:11:39.900 align:middle line:84%
I just-- I didn't know
what I was back then,

00:11:39.900 --> 00:11:43.380 align:middle line:84%
but I just felt like
everything was pretty--

00:11:43.380 --> 00:11:45.210 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you feel
like when you're part

00:11:45.210 --> 00:11:47.180 align:middle line:90%
of a path that has a purpose.

00:11:47.180 --> 00:11:49.180 align:middle line:84%
And that's kind of what
I felt when I was a kid.

00:11:49.180 --> 00:11:51.630 align:middle line:84%
I didn't understand what it
was, and maybe I still don't.

00:11:51.630 --> 00:11:53.560 align:middle line:84%
But I felt like that
when I was a kid.

00:11:53.560 --> 00:11:56.160 align:middle line:84%
Because I remember in elementary
school, one of my teachers,

00:11:56.160 --> 00:11:58.080 align:middle line:84%
I forgot what class
it was, he asked,

00:11:58.080 --> 00:12:02.610 align:middle line:84%
who believes that their
lives has a purpose?

00:12:02.610 --> 00:12:04.643 align:middle line:84%
And not a lot of people
raised their hands.

00:12:04.643 --> 00:12:05.560 align:middle line:90%
And I was one of them.

00:12:05.560 --> 00:12:05.740 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:12:05.740 --> 00:12:06.610 align:middle line:90%
And like, what's the purpose?

00:12:06.610 --> 00:12:07.410 align:middle line:90%
I have no idea.

00:12:07.410 --> 00:12:08.045 align:middle line:90%


00:12:08.045 --> 00:12:10.170 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: I don't know, eat
some more pizza tomorrow?

00:12:10.170 --> 00:12:11.138 align:middle line:90%
I have no idea.

00:12:11.138 --> 00:12:12.180 align:middle line:90%
But I did feel like that.

00:12:12.180 --> 00:12:13.220 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But you
inherently understood that.

00:12:13.220 --> 00:12:14.020 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: For sure.

00:12:14.020 --> 00:12:16.860 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's start
getting into what happened.

00:12:16.860 --> 00:12:18.555 align:middle line:90%
OK, so you're in America.

00:12:18.555 --> 00:12:19.680 align:middle line:90%
Your parents reestablished.

00:12:19.680 --> 00:12:21.060 align:middle line:90%
What did they end up doing here?

00:12:21.060 --> 00:12:22.680 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Horrible jobs.

00:12:22.680 --> 00:12:24.090 align:middle line:10%
I mean, just like most--

00:12:24.090 --> 00:12:27.300 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: After being
relatively privileged in China.

00:12:27.300 --> 00:12:28.980 align:middle line:10%
What kind of horrible
jobs did they do?

00:12:28.980 --> 00:12:31.500 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: I mean, my mom
worked at a sewing shop.

00:12:31.500 --> 00:12:33.180 align:middle line:84%
And I remember one
day she came home,

00:12:33.180 --> 00:12:36.000 align:middle line:84%
and she had a needle
through her finger.

00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:37.300 align:middle line:90%
It was just horrendous.

00:12:37.300 --> 00:12:38.520 align:middle line:90%
It was low pay.

00:12:38.520 --> 00:12:39.390 align:middle line:90%
It was hard labor.

00:12:39.390 --> 00:12:41.340 align:middle line:84%
My dad worked at a
restaurant as a waiter.

00:12:41.340 --> 00:12:42.450 align:middle line:90%
Because we came in--

00:12:42.450 --> 00:12:45.240 align:middle line:84%
I think he came with
a study abroad visa.

00:12:45.240 --> 00:12:48.060 align:middle line:84%
So he was attending school
at University of Tennessee.

00:12:48.060 --> 00:12:49.050 align:middle line:90%
And it was just--

00:12:49.050 --> 00:12:52.680 align:middle line:84%
we living in a house that
was called China House.

00:12:52.680 --> 00:12:54.753 align:middle line:84%
Now it sounds kind
of racist, but it was

00:12:54.753 --> 00:12:55.920 align:middle line:90%
just full of Chinese people.

00:12:55.920 --> 00:12:57.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Did they
speak English?

00:12:57.290 --> 00:12:57.690 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yeah.

00:12:57.690 --> 00:12:58.880 align:middle line:90%
My dad spoke English.

00:12:58.880 --> 00:12:58.980 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:12:58.980 --> 00:13:01.355 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: My dad, he actually
taught English back in China.

00:13:01.355 --> 00:13:02.400 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:13:02.400 --> 00:13:03.510 align:middle line:10%
>>CHEN: My mom did not.

00:13:03.510 --> 00:13:03.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:13:03.780 --> 00:13:04.980 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: And then
of course, I came.

00:13:04.980 --> 00:13:06.200 align:middle line:90%
I picked it up pretty quickly.

00:13:06.200 --> 00:13:06.460 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, right.

00:13:06.460 --> 00:13:08.793 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: But I mean, it was
pretty bad living conditions.

00:13:08.793 --> 00:13:10.410 align:middle line:90%
We all lived in one studio.

00:13:10.410 --> 00:13:14.100 align:middle line:84%
I remember we had a leisure
activity every weekend

00:13:14.100 --> 00:13:15.715 align:middle line:84%
where we'd go to
the local library,

00:13:15.715 --> 00:13:18.090 align:middle line:84%
like, every single person in
the house go to the library,

00:13:18.090 --> 00:13:19.507 align:middle line:84%
not for fun-- oh,
I guess for fun,

00:13:19.507 --> 00:13:22.650 align:middle line:84%
but mainly because we set
off roach bombs in the house

00:13:22.650 --> 00:13:23.860 align:middle line:90%
every week.

00:13:23.860 --> 00:13:27.870 align:middle line:84%
And you come back, and it just
like the "Night of the Living

00:13:27.870 --> 00:13:29.220 align:middle line:90%
Dead" or roaches everywhere.

00:13:29.220 --> 00:13:30.780 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So it was somewhere
free to go while the roaches

00:13:30.780 --> 00:13:31.822 align:middle line:90%
died off in your home.

00:13:31.822 --> 00:13:32.294 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:13:32.294 --> 00:13:33.240 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: It was just horrendous.

00:13:33.240 --> 00:13:34.660 align:middle line:90%
So now I moved to New York City.

00:13:34.660 --> 00:13:36.000 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, roaches, whatever.

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:37.330 align:middle line:90%
Grew up with them.

00:13:37.330 --> 00:13:38.130 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:13:38.130 --> 00:13:39.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So OK.

00:13:39.430 --> 00:13:42.240 align:middle line:84%
Now, we start getting into
the story that a lot of people

00:13:42.240 --> 00:13:44.220 align:middle line:90%
will be fascinated about.

00:13:44.220 --> 00:13:46.860 align:middle line:84%
Now in terms of the
Qigong that we're

00:13:46.860 --> 00:13:49.330 align:middle line:84%
going to be talking about,
so your parents went on.

00:13:49.330 --> 00:13:50.130 align:middle line:90%
You went on.

00:13:50.130 --> 00:13:50.850 align:middle line:90%
You learned your English.

00:13:50.850 --> 00:13:52.308 align:middle line:84%
You went through
the school system.

00:13:52.308 --> 00:13:53.200 align:middle line:90%
Everybody made do.

00:13:53.200 --> 00:13:54.000 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yes

00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:55.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you
started finding your way.

00:13:55.890 --> 00:13:58.255 align:middle line:84%
By college, you were
starting to find that things

00:13:58.255 --> 00:13:59.130 align:middle line:90%
weren't working well.

00:13:59.130 --> 00:14:00.840 align:middle line:84%
You went through a bit of a
depression, it sounds like?

00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:01.220 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yes.

00:14:01.220 --> 00:14:01.480 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:14:01.480 --> 00:14:01.770 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:14:01.770 --> 00:14:03.520 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And we'll
get into that.

00:14:03.520 --> 00:14:06.540 align:middle line:84%
And meanwhile, your mother,
and your mother and father

00:14:06.540 --> 00:14:09.040 align:middle line:84%
both had had an experience
with Falun Gong?

00:14:09.040 --> 00:14:09.840 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yes.

00:14:09.840 --> 00:14:10.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:14:10.640 --> 00:14:12.850 align:middle line:84%
Explain what that is and
where they had learned this.

00:14:12.850 --> 00:14:14.010 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Sure.

00:14:14.010 --> 00:14:17.200 align:middle line:84%
Well, Qigong in general,
let me just start from there

00:14:17.200 --> 00:14:19.620 align:middle line:84%
because a lot of
people may not know.

00:14:19.620 --> 00:14:21.600 align:middle line:90%
In China, "Qi" means energy.

00:14:21.600 --> 00:14:23.610 align:middle line:90%
And "Gong" means the practice.

00:14:23.610 --> 00:14:28.170 align:middle line:84%
And it's very, very
common exercise in China.

00:14:28.170 --> 00:14:30.990 align:middle line:84%
Most people probably
here have heard of--

00:14:30.990 --> 00:14:33.270 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We've seen the
videos of massive squares

00:14:33.270 --> 00:14:34.110 align:middle line:90%
and parks full of people.

00:14:34.110 --> 00:14:34.350 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yes.

00:14:34.350 --> 00:14:34.470 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:14:34.470 --> 00:14:34.850 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:14:34.850 --> 00:14:37.650 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: But probably the most
popular type of Qigong people

00:14:37.650 --> 00:14:40.860 align:middle line:84%
probably know about is Tai
Chi as a form of Qigong.

00:14:40.860 --> 00:14:43.613 align:middle line:84%
So Qigong always been
really popular in Chinese

00:14:43.613 --> 00:14:45.030 align:middle line:84%
throughout history,
but especially

00:14:45.030 --> 00:14:46.950 align:middle line:90%
so during the '80s and '90s.

00:14:46.950 --> 00:14:50.220 align:middle line:84%
That's when it just exploded
with Qigong Masters popping up

00:14:50.220 --> 00:14:55.130 align:middle line:84%
all over the place and with
legit supernatural powers.

00:14:55.130 --> 00:14:55.930 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, yeah.

00:14:55.930 --> 00:14:58.510 align:middle line:84%
I've seen some personally
from a master of that.

00:14:58.510 --> 00:14:59.310 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yeah.

00:14:59.310 --> 00:15:00.490 align:middle line:90%
And they were able to heal.

00:15:00.490 --> 00:15:02.365 align:middle line:84%
And they were well, you
know, heat things up.

00:15:02.365 --> 00:15:03.810 align:middle line:90%
It was crazy stuff.

00:15:03.810 --> 00:15:05.910 align:middle line:84%
So everybody in China was
really getting into it,

00:15:05.910 --> 00:15:07.285 align:middle line:84%
because Chinese
people, one thing

00:15:07.285 --> 00:15:11.010 align:middle line:84%
we love more than anything
is our health, especially

00:15:11.010 --> 00:15:12.360 align:middle line:90%
the older people.

00:15:12.360 --> 00:15:13.902 align:middle line:84%
Like you say, you
see them in parks.

00:15:13.902 --> 00:15:15.360 align:middle line:84%
Go to China now,
you see the parks.

00:15:15.360 --> 00:15:15.407 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:15:15.407 --> 00:15:16.365 align:middle line:90%
It was very impressive.

00:15:16.365 --> 00:15:17.400 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: It's everywhere.

00:15:17.400 --> 00:15:20.460 align:middle line:84%
But especially popular
was the '80s and '90s.

00:15:20.460 --> 00:15:22.680 align:middle line:84%
And that's when just
tons of it came out.

00:15:22.680 --> 00:15:25.410 align:middle line:84%
And Falun Gong was one of these
Qigong meditation exercises

00:15:25.410 --> 00:15:28.770 align:middle line:90%
that came out in 1992.

00:15:28.770 --> 00:15:32.540 align:middle line:84%
But what was different was
that after three years,

00:15:32.540 --> 00:15:35.730 align:middle line:84%
over 100 million Chinese people
were practicing this Qigong

00:15:35.730 --> 00:15:38.810 align:middle line:84%
meditation, which is the fastest
growing Qigong in the history.

00:15:38.810 --> 00:15:39.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: 100 million.

00:15:39.120 --> 00:15:39.850 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: 100 million.

00:15:39.850 --> 00:15:40.130 align:middle line:90%
Imagine.

00:15:40.130 --> 00:15:42.480 align:middle line:84%
That's like almost a tenth
of China's population.

00:15:42.480 --> 00:15:43.342 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:15:43.342 --> 00:15:44.550 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: And it was everybody.

00:15:44.550 --> 00:15:47.970 align:middle line:84%
People with normal jobs to high
government officials, everybody

00:15:47.970 --> 00:15:54.480 align:middle line:84%
was practicing because so many
people had health benefits

00:15:54.480 --> 00:15:56.970 align:middle line:84%
because they were doing
these meditation exercises,

00:15:56.970 --> 00:15:59.340 align:middle line:84%
and that's why they
believed it so much.

00:15:59.340 --> 00:16:03.630 align:middle line:84%
And the government actually
promoted it for a long time.

00:16:03.630 --> 00:16:05.210 align:middle line:90%
Because they were like, well--

00:16:05.210 --> 00:16:05.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Keep people health.

00:16:05.960 --> 00:16:07.377 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: People are
healthy, and we

00:16:07.377 --> 00:16:11.140 align:middle line:84%
don't have to spend as much
on medical care and all that.

00:16:11.140 --> 00:16:14.910 align:middle line:84%
So there were so many government
awards given to Falun Gong.

00:16:14.910 --> 00:16:17.940 align:middle line:84%
But then in 1997,
they took a census

00:16:17.940 --> 00:16:21.210 align:middle line:84%
and realized, oh my gosh, over
100 million Chinese people

00:16:21.210 --> 00:16:22.470 align:middle line:90%
were practicing this.

00:16:22.470 --> 00:16:27.330 align:middle line:84%
And that's why in 1999, they
decided to ban the exercise.

00:16:27.330 --> 00:16:29.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But one
moment on that.

00:16:29.370 --> 00:16:30.900 align:middle line:84%
Going back to
Qigong, wasn't that

00:16:30.900 --> 00:16:32.620 align:middle line:84%
already ubiquitous
in Chinese culture?

00:16:32.620 --> 00:16:33.420 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yes.

00:16:33.420 --> 00:16:35.230 align:middle line:84%
But no Qigong has
ever been as popular.

00:16:35.230 --> 00:16:36.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I see.

00:16:36.030 --> 00:16:38.110 align:middle line:84%
So it was the sheer
strength in numbers--

00:16:38.110 --> 00:16:38.910 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yes.

00:16:38.910 --> 00:16:40.260 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: At the way
this had caught on?

00:16:40.260 --> 00:16:40.740 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Exactly.

00:16:40.740 --> 00:16:43.198 align:middle line:84%
And also most people don't know
this about Qigong exercise,

00:16:43.198 --> 00:16:48.060 align:middle line:84%
but every single Qigong
exercise is paired

00:16:48.060 --> 00:16:49.920 align:middle line:90%
with a philosophical thought.

00:16:49.920 --> 00:16:53.520 align:middle line:84%
The exercise itself, just
like in the Shaolin Temple,

00:16:53.520 --> 00:16:55.990 align:middle line:84%
they do a form of
Qigong as well.

00:16:55.990 --> 00:16:57.990 align:middle line:84%
Their martial arts is
actually a form of Qigong.

00:16:57.990 --> 00:17:00.370 align:middle line:84%
There's a breathing
exercise and all that,

00:17:00.370 --> 00:17:02.320 align:middle line:84%
and it's paired with
Buddhist philosophy.

00:17:02.320 --> 00:17:06.150 align:middle line:84%
And Tai Chi is paired
with Taoist philosophy.

00:17:06.150 --> 00:17:08.670 align:middle line:84%
So Falun Gong is also paired
with Buddhist philosophy

00:17:08.670 --> 00:17:11.460 align:middle line:84%
as well, and it's based on the
principles of truthfulness,

00:17:11.460 --> 00:17:12.930 align:middle line:90%
compassion, and tolerance.

00:17:12.930 --> 00:17:15.000 align:middle line:84%
So there's the three
major founding principles

00:17:15.000 --> 00:17:15.810 align:middle line:90%
of Falun Gong.

00:17:15.810 --> 00:17:17.579 align:middle line:84%
So people who were
practicing it not only

00:17:17.579 --> 00:17:20.400 align:middle line:84%
got healthier, they
were becoming better.

00:17:20.400 --> 00:17:21.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, you
would think this

00:17:21.900 --> 00:17:24.490 align:middle line:84%
would be desirable on all
levels for any government

00:17:24.490 --> 00:17:25.290 align:middle line:90%
in the world.

00:17:25.290 --> 00:17:26.873 align:middle line:84%
I mean, Bhutan would
certainly dig it.

00:17:26.873 --> 00:17:27.673 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Right.

00:17:27.673 --> 00:17:29.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But China
was not digging it.

00:17:29.470 --> 00:17:30.270 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: No, no.

00:17:30.270 --> 00:17:31.070 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't.

00:17:31.070 --> 00:17:34.620 align:middle line:84%
Because most people
in China are atheist.

00:17:34.620 --> 00:17:39.000 align:middle line:84%
And the Communist Party actually
doesn't allow the belief

00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:40.545 align:middle line:90%
of even time travel and ghosts.

00:17:40.545 --> 00:17:41.670 align:middle line:90%
I'm not even kidding about.

00:17:41.670 --> 00:17:43.590 align:middle line:90%
This is actually a huge news.

00:17:43.590 --> 00:17:44.920 align:middle line:90%
I think it was a few years ago.

00:17:44.920 --> 00:17:46.350 align:middle line:84%
You can't see "Back
to the Future"

00:17:46.350 --> 00:17:49.140 align:middle line:84%
in China because it
talks about time travel.

00:17:49.140 --> 00:17:51.937 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But they do
explore UFO phenomena.

00:17:51.937 --> 00:17:53.520 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: I'm not quite
sure what they--

00:17:53.520 --> 00:17:54.790 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Well, they do--

00:17:54.790 --> 00:17:55.590 align:middle line:90%
well, anyway.

00:17:55.590 --> 00:17:56.920 align:middle line:90%
That's a whole other community.

00:17:56.920 --> 00:17:57.510 align:middle line:90%
They'll explore that.

00:17:57.510 --> 00:17:58.860 align:middle line:84%
Maybe that's more
on the low down

00:17:58.860 --> 00:18:00.610 align:middle line:84%
and they don't share
that with the people.

00:18:00.610 --> 00:18:03.060 align:middle line:84%
But they don't explain any
kind of invisible phenomena.

00:18:03.060 --> 00:18:04.230 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Right.

00:18:04.230 --> 00:18:07.260 align:middle line:84%
So any time any time
people in the country

00:18:07.260 --> 00:18:09.480 align:middle line:84%
start having their
own belief, it's

00:18:09.480 --> 00:18:11.610 align:middle line:84%
a problem for the
Communist Party.

00:18:11.610 --> 00:18:13.470 align:middle line:84%
So they wanted to just
completely nix it.

00:18:13.470 --> 00:18:16.230 align:middle line:84%
So in '99, what they did
was in Tiananmen Square,

00:18:16.230 --> 00:18:18.960 align:middle line:84%
they set up an
elaborate-- basically,

00:18:18.960 --> 00:18:22.210 align:middle line:84%
a hoax where they have people
set themselves on fire wearing

00:18:22.210 --> 00:18:23.060 align:middle line:90%
fireproof clothing.

00:18:23.060 --> 00:18:23.640 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, the
immolation thing, yeah.

00:18:23.640 --> 00:18:25.020 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: And they said,
hey, you know what?

00:18:25.020 --> 00:18:26.020 align:middle line:84%
These are Falun
Gong practitioners.

00:18:26.020 --> 00:18:27.210 align:middle line:90%
They're killing themselves.

00:18:27.210 --> 00:18:29.085 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And then they
put it on national TV

00:18:29.085 --> 00:18:30.570 align:middle line:90%
that these guys are whack jobs.

00:18:30.570 --> 00:18:31.330 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: National TV, yes.

00:18:31.330 --> 00:18:33.510 align:middle line:84%
And there's a great
documentary called "False Fire"

00:18:33.510 --> 00:18:35.085 align:middle line:84%
that just blew
through the entire--

00:18:35.085 --> 00:18:36.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, "False Fire."

00:18:36.210 --> 00:18:36.990 align:middle line:90%
Is it on YouTube?

00:18:36.990 --> 00:18:37.610 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: It's on YouTube.

00:18:37.610 --> 00:18:38.410 align:middle line:90%
It's everywhere.

00:18:38.410 --> 00:18:41.562 align:middle line:84%
But it kind of blew through the
entire lie of the government.

00:18:41.562 --> 00:18:44.020 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I'm so glad to know
people weren't really setting

00:18:44.020 --> 00:18:44.300 align:middle line:90%
themselves on fire.

00:18:44.300 --> 00:18:45.630 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: No, no, no, no, no.

00:18:45.630 --> 00:18:48.450 align:middle line:84%
Because in Falun Gong we
believe we can't kill lives.

00:18:48.450 --> 00:18:49.250 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:18:49.250 --> 00:18:50.370 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yourself is alive.

00:18:50.370 --> 00:18:51.400 align:middle line:90%
You can't kill yourself.

00:18:51.400 --> 00:18:51.600 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:18:51.600 --> 00:18:53.160 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: So there's no Falun
Gong practitioner that

00:18:53.160 --> 00:18:54.030 align:middle line:90%
would actually kill themselves.

00:18:54.030 --> 00:18:54.830 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:18:54.830 --> 00:18:57.840 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: You can see on camera a
police actually hitting someone

00:18:57.840 --> 00:19:01.500 align:middle line:84%
over the head, one of the person
who set themselves on fire,

00:19:01.500 --> 00:19:03.930 align:middle line:84%
hit him over the head
and the baton even broke.

00:19:03.930 --> 00:19:05.520 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is
crazy documentary.

00:19:05.520 --> 00:19:07.630 align:middle line:84%
But it's just blew through
the entire narrative.

00:19:07.630 --> 00:19:08.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:19:08.430 --> 00:19:08.970 align:middle line:90%
"False Fire" on YouTube.

00:19:08.970 --> 00:19:09.720 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: "False Fire," yes.

00:19:09.720 --> 00:19:10.220 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So we have that.

00:19:10.220 --> 00:19:11.020 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:19:11.020 --> 00:19:17.270 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: So '99, right before
this all happened, my parents--

00:19:17.270 --> 00:19:19.830 align:middle line:90%
we were living in Illinois.

00:19:19.830 --> 00:19:20.680 align:middle line:90%
I was in college.

00:19:20.680 --> 00:19:22.680 align:middle line:84%
And it was kind of a
crazy dynamic, our family.

00:19:22.680 --> 00:19:26.640 align:middle line:84%
Because my dad had the
worst temper of anybody.

00:19:26.640 --> 00:19:28.630 align:middle line:90%
He's just-- guy was just mean.

00:19:28.630 --> 00:19:29.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:19:29.430 --> 00:19:32.140 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: It was so incredibly
horrendous to live

00:19:32.140 --> 00:19:33.420 align:middle line:90%
in the household.

00:19:33.420 --> 00:19:35.290 align:middle line:84%
So I basically
escaped to college.

00:19:35.290 --> 00:19:37.050 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want to
ever come back home.

00:19:37.050 --> 00:19:38.280 align:middle line:84%
I felt bad for my
mother, because she's

00:19:38.280 --> 00:19:39.240 align:middle line:90%
the gentlest person ever.

00:19:39.240 --> 00:19:39.800 align:middle line:90%
And she--

00:19:39.800 --> 00:19:40.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Was he
abusive to you guys?

00:19:40.980 --> 00:19:41.780 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Verbally.

00:19:41.780 --> 00:19:43.970 align:middle line:84%
Not physically, but just
incredibly verbally--

00:19:43.970 --> 00:19:45.720 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --which can
destroy your spirit.

00:19:45.720 --> 00:19:47.820 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: It's horrible.

00:19:47.820 --> 00:19:50.190 align:middle line:84%
So I escaped, and my
mom was still there.

00:19:50.190 --> 00:19:52.170 align:middle line:84%
Basically cursing at
us every single day,

00:19:52.170 --> 00:19:54.500 align:middle line:84%
and my mom was
getting really sick.

00:19:54.500 --> 00:19:56.250 align:middle line:84%
And this is something
they didn't tell me.

00:19:56.250 --> 00:19:59.250 align:middle line:84%
My mom was seeing a doctor
in the nearby hospital in St.

00:19:59.250 --> 00:20:01.800 align:middle line:84%
Louis every single
week, and it turns out

00:20:01.800 --> 00:20:03.120 align:middle line:90%
she had terminal throat cancer.

00:20:03.120 --> 00:20:04.710 align:middle line:90%
And she did literally--

00:20:04.710 --> 00:20:06.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Did she ever
speak back to him?

00:20:06.810 --> 00:20:07.170 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: No.

00:20:07.170 --> 00:20:07.970 align:middle line:90%
She didn't.

00:20:07.970 --> 00:20:10.208 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's the-- that's
why I'm thinking, yeah.

00:20:10.208 --> 00:20:11.250 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: She just took it.

00:20:11.250 --> 00:20:13.320 align:middle line:84%
And then, they never
told me about this.

00:20:13.320 --> 00:20:15.120 align:middle line:84%
And then so she was
actually at that time

00:20:15.120 --> 00:20:17.877 align:middle line:84%
practicing another
Qigong meditation.

00:20:17.877 --> 00:20:19.460 align:middle line:84%
And then this Qigong
practice required

00:20:19.460 --> 00:20:22.370 align:middle line:84%
her to send money to the Qigong
master every single week.

00:20:22.370 --> 00:20:25.037 align:middle line:84%
And my dad was getting even more
mad, because he was like, well,

00:20:25.037 --> 00:20:30.540 align:middle line:84%
why are you wasting all our
money on this whackery stuff?

00:20:30.540 --> 00:20:33.170 align:middle line:84%
And so finally, my mom was
like, oh, yeah, this practice

00:20:33.170 --> 00:20:33.970 align:middle line:90%
is not working.

00:20:33.970 --> 00:20:35.950 align:middle line:84%
And then she saw an
ad for Falun Gong.

00:20:35.950 --> 00:20:37.520 align:middle line:90%
And then she called the ad.

00:20:37.520 --> 00:20:40.440 align:middle line:84%
And two people, volunteers, came
in from St. Louis, Missouri,

00:20:40.440 --> 00:20:42.930 align:middle line:84%
spent two days with
us, and taught everyone

00:20:42.930 --> 00:20:45.500 align:middle line:84%
the meditation exercise
completely free,

00:20:45.500 --> 00:20:46.730 align:middle line:90%
and then they left.

00:20:46.730 --> 00:20:48.120 align:middle line:90%
And that's it.

00:20:48.120 --> 00:20:51.080 align:middle line:84%
And then my mom
started practicing.

00:20:51.080 --> 00:20:53.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What is the signature
of it that's so powerful?

00:20:53.790 --> 00:20:55.610 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: Well, it's
just the way you feel.

00:20:55.610 --> 00:20:58.010 align:middle line:84%
Like, sometimes, when people
practice the meditation

00:20:58.010 --> 00:21:00.785 align:middle line:84%
exercise for the first time,
they feel such crazy energy.

00:21:00.785 --> 00:21:02.660 align:middle line:84%
And that's what my mom
feel that first night.

00:21:02.660 --> 00:21:06.040 align:middle line:84%
She told me she felt all
the energy in her head,

00:21:06.040 --> 00:21:07.240 align:middle line:90%
not like she's imagining.

00:21:07.240 --> 00:21:08.650 align:middle line:84%
She actually felt
it in her head.

00:21:08.650 --> 00:21:09.450 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:21:09.450 --> 00:21:10.020 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: It's my mother.

00:21:10.020 --> 00:21:11.228 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to not believe her.

00:21:11.228 --> 00:21:13.080 align:middle line:84%
So she felt the
energy in her head.

00:21:13.080 --> 00:21:17.270 align:middle line:84%
And then she felt
like somebody was

00:21:17.270 --> 00:21:20.840 align:middle line:84%
almost like ripping her hair
off on another dimension, kind

00:21:20.840 --> 00:21:24.410 align:middle line:90%
of healing her entire upper--

00:21:24.410 --> 00:21:26.570 align:middle line:90%
right here-- upper region here.

00:21:26.570 --> 00:21:28.743 align:middle line:90%
And then she was fine.

00:21:28.743 --> 00:21:29.660 align:middle line:90%
And then she was fine.

00:21:29.660 --> 00:21:30.952 align:middle line:90%
She didn't go back to hospital.

00:21:30.952 --> 00:21:32.270 align:middle line:90%
She was completely fine.

00:21:32.270 --> 00:21:33.500 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Cancer went
into total remission?

00:21:33.500 --> 00:21:33.800 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yes.

00:21:33.800 --> 00:21:34.600 align:middle line:90%
Completely gone.

00:21:34.600 --> 00:21:35.496 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:21:35.496 --> 00:21:37.190 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: And she's been here--

00:21:37.190 --> 00:21:38.530 align:middle line:90%
'99, like 20 years.

00:21:38.530 --> 00:21:39.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:21:39.330 --> 00:21:39.940 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, yeah.

00:21:39.940 --> 00:21:40.815 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: 20 years now.

00:21:40.815 --> 00:21:43.190 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, which is
amazing, and wonderful,

00:21:43.190 --> 00:21:44.990 align:middle line:84%
and wonderful for you
that you still have

00:21:44.990 --> 00:21:47.330 align:middle line:90%
your gentle-hearted mother.

00:21:47.330 --> 00:21:50.300 align:middle line:84%
But the actual practice
itself, is this something

00:21:50.300 --> 00:21:52.740 align:middle line:84%
that-- because I know our
viewers right now are saying,

00:21:52.740 --> 00:21:54.680 align:middle line:90%
where do we find the Falun Gong?

00:21:54.680 --> 00:21:56.510 align:middle line:84%
So let's just talk
about that for a moment.

00:21:56.510 --> 00:21:59.068 align:middle line:84%
How would people connect, then,
with the Falun Gong practice?

00:21:59.068 --> 00:22:00.860 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: The great thing
about this practice

00:22:00.860 --> 00:22:05.420 align:middle line:84%
is that it's 100% free, which
is, like, you never see that.

00:22:05.420 --> 00:22:08.630 align:middle line:84%
So the founder who brought it
out, he doesn't want any money.

00:22:08.630 --> 00:22:09.823 align:middle line:90%
I mean, he prints books.

00:22:09.823 --> 00:22:11.990 align:middle line:10%
So you have to pay for the
books if you want a book.

00:22:11.990 --> 00:22:13.820 align:middle line:10%
But all the stuff
is online for free.

00:22:13.820 --> 00:22:17.080 align:middle line:10%
So you can go online
FalunDafa.org.

00:22:17.080 --> 00:22:18.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Dafa, yeah.

00:22:18.050 --> 00:22:19.550 align:middle line:84%
Because the people see
that online and think,

00:22:19.550 --> 00:22:20.752 align:middle line:90%
well, that looks different.

00:22:20.752 --> 00:22:21.710 align:middle line:90%
Is that the same thing?

00:22:21.710 --> 00:22:22.250 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: It's the same thing.

00:22:22.250 --> 00:22:23.000 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Falun Dafa.

00:22:23.000 --> 00:22:23.370 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:22:23.370 --> 00:22:24.328 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: The Falun Dafa.

00:22:24.328 --> 00:22:26.340 align:middle line:84%
Dafa is the principle,
and the Falun Gong

00:22:26.340 --> 00:22:28.010 align:middle line:84%
is the actual
meditation exercise.

00:22:28.010 --> 00:22:30.290 align:middle line:84%
Because like I said, there's
a Buddhist philosophy

00:22:30.290 --> 00:22:32.130 align:middle line:84%
and principles
connected to it as well.

00:22:32.130 --> 00:22:33.110 align:middle line:90%
So everything's free.

00:22:33.110 --> 00:22:34.520 align:middle line:90%
You can download the exercises.

00:22:34.520 --> 00:22:35.420 align:middle line:90%
You can learn it.

00:22:35.420 --> 00:22:37.730 align:middle line:84%
You can go to any of the
practice sites, which

00:22:37.730 --> 00:22:38.880 align:middle line:90%
are all around the world.

00:22:38.880 --> 00:22:40.130 align:middle line:90%
And people teach you for free.

00:22:40.130 --> 00:22:42.590 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to ever spend
a single penny ever for this.

00:22:42.590 --> 00:22:43.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's a real story.

00:22:43.310 --> 00:22:44.110 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yes.

00:22:44.110 --> 00:22:46.443 align:middle line:84%
And that's why it makes
this really something

00:22:46.443 --> 00:22:47.610 align:middle line:90%
different than anybody else.

00:22:47.610 --> 00:22:49.290 align:middle line:84%
Because if you go to
China at that time,

00:22:49.290 --> 00:22:51.140 align:middle line:84%
people were charging
for classes,

00:22:51.140 --> 00:22:52.850 align:middle line:84%
charging for this,
and that, and this.

00:22:52.850 --> 00:22:56.370 align:middle line:84%
But the founder, Mr. Li
Hongzhi, charges nothing.

00:22:56.370 --> 00:22:59.940 align:middle line:84%
And then of course, there's
a lot of bad narratives

00:22:59.940 --> 00:23:01.940 align:middle line:84%
out there started by the
Communist Party saying,

00:23:01.940 --> 00:23:04.460 align:middle line:84%
oh, hey, Falun Gong
practitioners, they're

00:23:04.460 --> 00:23:06.050 align:middle line:90%
all being paid.

00:23:06.050 --> 00:23:08.870 align:middle line:84%
Because we go on parades
to talk about what's

00:23:08.870 --> 00:23:09.878 align:middle line:90%
happening in China.

00:23:09.878 --> 00:23:11.420 align:middle line:84%
And then, oh, they're
all being paid.

00:23:11.420 --> 00:23:13.700 align:middle line:10%
They're all-- like,
no one's paying me.

00:23:13.700 --> 00:23:15.510 align:middle line:90%
I don't get money from anything.

00:23:15.510 --> 00:23:19.230 align:middle line:84%
I just do it out of my
conscience, because I love it.

00:23:19.230 --> 00:23:20.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:23:20.030 --> 00:23:20.830 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:23:20.830 --> 00:23:22.790 align:middle line:84%
And so OK, now
we're going to start

00:23:22.790 --> 00:23:24.320 align:middle line:90%
crossing the story over a bit.

00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:27.710 align:middle line:84%
We're going to go into Chinese
propaganda machines, machinery.

00:23:27.710 --> 00:23:29.050 align:middle line:90%
The 50 Cent-- what's it called?

00:23:29.050 --> 00:23:29.330 align:middle line:90%
Not squad?

00:23:29.330 --> 00:23:29.840 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: 50 Cent Army.

00:23:29.840 --> 00:23:30.240 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Army.

00:23:30.240 --> 00:23:31.040 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Sure.

00:23:31.040 --> 00:23:32.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: 50 Cent Army.

00:23:32.030 --> 00:23:34.070 align:middle line:84%
We're going to tie it
together with Falun Gong.

00:23:34.070 --> 00:23:34.490 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: OK.

00:23:34.490 --> 00:23:36.323 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And we're
going to tie it together

00:23:36.323 --> 00:23:38.780 align:middle line:84%
with an industry that's
pretty darn dark, OK?

00:23:38.780 --> 00:23:39.740 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Sure.

00:23:39.740 --> 00:23:42.597 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So your mother was
able to heal herself of cancer.

00:23:42.597 --> 00:23:44.180 align:middle line:84%
I just want to set
it up a little bit.

00:23:44.180 --> 00:23:46.430 align:middle line:84%
And she told you,
you need to start

00:23:46.430 --> 00:23:47.900 align:middle line:90%
learning this art yourself now.

00:23:47.900 --> 00:23:48.700 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: She did.

00:23:48.700 --> 00:23:51.830 align:middle line:84%
She told me I needed to start,
and I rejected it right away.

00:23:51.830 --> 00:23:57.470 align:middle line:84%
Because she kept pushing this
Qigong exercise on me before,

00:23:57.470 --> 00:23:58.610 align:middle line:90%
like, one after another.

00:23:58.610 --> 00:24:00.818 align:middle line:84%
And it got to the point
where I'm just so sick of it.

00:24:00.818 --> 00:24:03.020 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, do not talk to
me about any of this stuff.

00:24:03.020 --> 00:24:04.520 align:middle line:84%
I don't want anything
to do with it.

00:24:04.520 --> 00:24:06.740 align:middle line:84%
But being a Chinese mom,
she's like, no, you have to.

00:24:06.740 --> 00:24:07.000 align:middle line:90%
This is the way to stay.

00:24:07.000 --> 00:24:08.500 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But you're an
All-American kid at this point.

00:24:08.500 --> 00:24:08.870 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yeah.

00:24:08.870 --> 00:24:09.450 align:middle line:90%
I'm like leave me alone.

00:24:09.450 --> 00:24:11.720 align:middle line:84%
I need to go and get a pizza
or something like that.

00:24:11.720 --> 00:24:12.960 align:middle line:90%
Leave me alone.

00:24:12.960 --> 00:24:16.460 align:middle line:84%
So I was completely
just rejecting the idea

00:24:16.460 --> 00:24:18.870 align:middle line:84%
until I started having
my own breakdown.

00:24:18.870 --> 00:24:19.670 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Crisis

00:24:19.670 --> 00:24:20.480 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yeah, in college.

00:24:20.480 --> 00:24:22.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Why were
you depressed?

00:24:22.010 --> 00:24:23.718 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: It was my
junior year in college.

00:24:23.718 --> 00:24:26.780 align:middle line:84%
And I remember at that point
I knew what I wanted in life.

00:24:26.780 --> 00:24:27.690 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to be--

00:24:27.690 --> 00:24:28.790 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Besides Dim Sum?

00:24:28.790 --> 00:24:30.240 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Besides all the food.

00:24:30.240 --> 00:24:32.190 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to be really popular.

00:24:32.190 --> 00:24:34.520 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to find a great girl.

00:24:34.520 --> 00:24:35.970 align:middle line:90%
Those were my things.

00:24:35.970 --> 00:24:36.770 align:middle line:90%
It was very, like--

00:24:36.770 --> 00:24:38.720 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they're not
huge goals, but they're

00:24:38.720 --> 00:24:39.100 align:middle line:90%
very Midwestern goals.

00:24:39.100 --> 00:24:40.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They're
normal kid goals.

00:24:40.240 --> 00:24:41.040 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:24:41.040 --> 00:24:42.560 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: So I wanted
all this stuff.

00:24:42.560 --> 00:24:45.020 align:middle line:84%
And then I remember this
one incident in college

00:24:45.020 --> 00:24:47.920 align:middle line:84%
where I had a friend who I felt
like he really had everything.

00:24:47.920 --> 00:24:50.390 align:middle line:84%
He was a good looking
guy, really popular, great

00:24:50.390 --> 00:24:54.800 align:middle line:84%
girlfriend, and then he
ended up killing himself.

00:24:54.800 --> 00:24:56.110 align:middle line:90%
And after that, I was just--

00:24:56.110 --> 00:24:57.980 align:middle line:84%
it was a big thing
for all of us.

00:24:57.980 --> 00:25:01.070 align:middle line:84%
And then after that I
was like, man, these

00:25:01.070 --> 00:25:04.310 align:middle line:84%
are all things I
really wanted in life.

00:25:04.310 --> 00:25:05.530 align:middle line:90%
And he had it all.

00:25:05.530 --> 00:25:09.710 align:middle line:84%
Then what if I have it all
and I'm still depressed?

00:25:09.710 --> 00:25:11.970 align:middle line:84%
And I just became more
and more depressed.

00:25:11.970 --> 00:25:15.620 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I started
to get into everything

00:25:15.620 --> 00:25:18.885 align:middle line:84%
from parapsychology, I
took a class in hypnosis.

00:25:18.885 --> 00:25:20.260 align:middle line:84%
I was doing all
this stuff to try

00:25:20.260 --> 00:25:23.830 align:middle line:84%
to find what is the
point of being here.

00:25:23.830 --> 00:25:27.625 align:middle line:84%
That was my entire thing
for about two years.

00:25:27.625 --> 00:25:29.500 align:middle line:84%
It got to a point where
I went home and said,

00:25:29.500 --> 00:25:31.990 align:middle line:90%
I want to drop out of college.

00:25:31.990 --> 00:25:33.760 align:middle line:84%
My parents were like
OK, sure, whatever.

00:25:33.760 --> 00:25:34.577 align:middle line:90%
That's fine.

00:25:34.577 --> 00:25:35.535 align:middle line:90%
Because at that point--

00:25:35.535 --> 00:25:36.640 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Didn't
tick your dad off?

00:25:36.640 --> 00:25:37.810 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: You know,
that's the great thing

00:25:37.810 --> 00:25:39.480 align:middle line:84%
about this practice
is that, like I said,

00:25:39.480 --> 00:25:41.180 align:middle line:84%
it's based on truthfulness,
compassion, and tolerance.

00:25:41.180 --> 00:25:42.510 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because they were
both doing it by this point?

00:25:42.510 --> 00:25:44.530 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: By that point, my dad--

00:25:44.530 --> 00:25:46.640 align:middle line:84%
he was yelling at my mom
everyday for doing it.

00:25:46.640 --> 00:25:48.348 align:middle line:84%
And at a certain point,
he was just like,

00:25:48.348 --> 00:25:49.348 align:middle line:90%
why she never mad at me?

00:25:49.348 --> 00:25:51.598 align:middle line:84%
And then finally he started
looking into this practice

00:25:51.598 --> 00:25:52.420 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:25:52.420 --> 00:25:56.155 align:middle line:84%
And now if you meet him,
he's the kindest guy.

00:25:56.155 --> 00:25:57.280 align:middle line:90%
No one would ever suspect--

00:25:57.280 --> 00:25:57.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I love it.

00:25:57.420 --> 00:25:57.660 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:25:57.660 --> 00:25:59.620 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: --this guy had
a huge, huge temper.

00:25:59.620 --> 00:26:03.390 align:middle line:84%
So he was just
completely changed.

00:26:03.390 --> 00:26:05.140 align:middle line:84%
And then so they were
both encouraging me.

00:26:05.140 --> 00:26:07.780 align:middle line:84%
They were like, well, maybe you
should look into this practice

00:26:07.780 --> 00:26:08.650 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:26:08.650 --> 00:26:09.530 align:middle line:90%
We're not trying to push you.

00:26:09.530 --> 00:26:10.330 align:middle line:90%
But they were.

00:26:10.330 --> 00:26:11.747 align:middle line:84%
Not trying to push
you, but if you

00:26:11.747 --> 00:26:14.122 align:middle line:84%
need to drop out of college,
take some time, that's fine.

00:26:14.122 --> 00:26:16.310 align:middle line:84%
So finally out I was at
a point where I was like,

00:26:16.310 --> 00:26:17.620 align:middle line:90%
you know what?

00:26:17.620 --> 00:26:18.790 align:middle line:90%
What I got to lose?

00:26:18.790 --> 00:26:21.580 align:middle line:84%
So I read the book more,
and I did the exercise more.

00:26:21.580 --> 00:26:23.450 align:middle line:84%
It's not like
overnight thing for me.

00:26:23.450 --> 00:26:25.180 align:middle line:84%
But after a long
time and interacting

00:26:25.180 --> 00:26:28.310 align:middle line:84%
with the people who practice it,
I was like, well, these people,

00:26:28.310 --> 00:26:29.560 align:middle line:90%
they are so kind.

00:26:29.560 --> 00:26:36.092 align:middle line:84%
And they are so sincere in
their wanting to help you.

00:26:36.092 --> 00:26:38.050 align:middle line:84%
And then I start getting
into it more and more.

00:26:38.050 --> 00:26:40.540 align:middle line:84%
And I realized, well,
this is really incredible.

00:26:40.540 --> 00:26:42.940 align:middle line:84%
And it kind of changed
your entire outlook

00:26:42.940 --> 00:26:46.520 align:middle line:84%
on the purpose of life
and why we're all here.

00:26:46.520 --> 00:26:50.650 align:middle line:84%
And then I became better
and then graduated college.

00:26:50.650 --> 00:26:52.532 align:middle line:84%
Took me five years,
but it happened.

00:26:52.532 --> 00:26:53.365 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's OK.

00:26:53.365 --> 00:26:55.540 align:middle line:90%
And you continued practicing?

00:26:55.540 --> 00:26:56.340 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yeah.

00:26:56.340 --> 00:26:58.160 align:middle line:84%
And I continued
practicing after college.

00:26:58.160 --> 00:27:00.100 align:middle line:84%
I started doing
human rights work.

00:27:00.100 --> 00:27:01.660 align:middle line:84%
So I did that for
about 12 years,

00:27:01.660 --> 00:27:04.990 align:middle line:84%
where just talking about
what was happening in China.

00:27:04.990 --> 00:27:07.390 align:middle line:84%
Because after the practice
became outlawed in China,

00:27:07.390 --> 00:27:09.100 align:middle line:84%
a lot of dark stuff
started happening.

00:27:09.100 --> 00:27:09.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:27:09.520 --> 00:27:11.020 align:middle line:84%
And that's where
the story comes in.

00:27:11.020 --> 00:27:14.590 align:middle line:84%
Let's start-- is it appropriate
to jump into the 50 Cent Army?

00:27:14.590 --> 00:27:15.400 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Sure.

00:27:15.400 --> 00:27:17.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Let's jump into that.

00:27:17.020 --> 00:27:18.010 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: Yeah, I
mean, most people

00:27:18.010 --> 00:27:19.510 align:middle line:84%
don't know what the
50 Cent Army is.

00:27:19.510 --> 00:27:22.870 align:middle line:84%
It's basically internet trolls
being paid by the government.

00:27:22.870 --> 00:27:25.930 align:middle line:84%
It's reported on by every
single major news outlet.

00:27:25.930 --> 00:27:27.390 align:middle line:90%
Sounds like, ooh, movie.

00:27:27.390 --> 00:27:27.730 align:middle line:90%
Sci Fi.

00:27:27.730 --> 00:27:27.900 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:27:27.900 --> 00:27:28.900 align:middle line:90%
It's actually real.

00:27:28.900 --> 00:27:33.100 align:middle line:84%
So they are paid $0.50 per
comment that they make that are

00:27:33.100 --> 00:27:35.558 align:middle line:84%
pro-China or negates
something that--

00:27:35.558 --> 00:27:37.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
good money in China.

00:27:37.100 --> 00:27:37.570 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yeah.

00:27:37.570 --> 00:27:38.170 align:middle line:90%
It's really good money.

00:27:38.170 --> 00:27:39.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You can
make a lot of money.

00:27:39.290 --> 00:27:40.090 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Right.

00:27:40.090 --> 00:27:42.550 align:middle line:84%
So they're on these
videos on YouTube,

00:27:42.550 --> 00:27:46.270 align:middle line:84%
or sites where they
find videos are maybe

00:27:46.270 --> 00:27:48.858 align:middle line:84%
pro-Taiwan independence,
pro-Tibet, and they comment.

00:27:48.858 --> 00:27:49.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Pro Falun Gong.

00:27:49.900 --> 00:27:50.860 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Pro-Falun Gong.

00:27:50.860 --> 00:27:53.310 align:middle line:84%
And they will comment,
and comment, and comment.

00:27:53.310 --> 00:27:54.170 align:middle line:90%
That's their job.

00:27:54.170 --> 00:27:54.970 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:27:54.970 --> 00:27:58.390 align:middle line:84%
So that's why you'll see a
lot of information online

00:27:58.390 --> 00:28:01.860 align:middle line:84%
that speaks out against
Taiwan, against Tibet,

00:28:01.860 --> 00:28:04.420 align:middle line:84%
and against Falun Gong,
against House Christians.

00:28:04.420 --> 00:28:07.000 align:middle line:84%
And that's mainly
done by these people.

00:28:07.000 --> 00:28:11.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So we start
weaving in the illegality

00:28:11.080 --> 00:28:13.160 align:middle line:90%
of the practice in China.

00:28:13.160 --> 00:28:15.880 align:middle line:90%
So there's a severe penalty.

00:28:15.880 --> 00:28:17.710 align:middle line:84%
You can go to prison
for practicing.

00:28:17.710 --> 00:28:18.460 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: It's worse than that.

00:28:18.460 --> 00:28:19.260 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:28:19.260 --> 00:28:20.950 align:middle line:84%
And so explain just
how bad it gets

00:28:20.950 --> 00:28:22.520 align:middle line:84%
and how people
have been treated.

00:28:22.520 --> 00:28:23.320 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Right.

00:28:23.320 --> 00:28:27.310 align:middle line:84%
So when the persecution
came, when the footage

00:28:27.310 --> 00:28:29.860 align:middle line:84%
of the Tiananmen
Square immolation

00:28:29.860 --> 00:28:33.010 align:middle line:90%
was everywhere in China--

00:28:33.010 --> 00:28:34.848 align:middle line:84%
by the way, really,
watch this documentary.

00:28:34.848 --> 00:28:36.140 align:middle line:90%
It just doesn't make any sense.

00:28:36.140 --> 00:28:37.030 align:middle line:84%
You're in middle of
Tiananmen Square.

00:28:37.030 --> 00:28:37.950 align:middle line:90%
People lit themselves on fire.

00:28:37.950 --> 00:28:40.617 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden, cameras show up
and fire extinguishers show up.

00:28:40.617 --> 00:28:41.740 align:middle line:90%
Like, really?

00:28:41.740 --> 00:28:43.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And again, that's
"False Fire" on YouTube.

00:28:43.200 --> 00:28:44.367 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: "False Fire," right.

00:28:44.367 --> 00:28:47.710 align:middle line:84%
And then so when that
happened, people in China

00:28:47.710 --> 00:28:50.470 align:middle line:84%
were Falun Gong
practitioners were like,

00:28:50.470 --> 00:28:52.180 align:middle line:90%
why are you locking us up?

00:28:52.180 --> 00:28:54.180 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you're
talking 100 million people?

00:28:54.180 --> 00:28:55.305 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: 100 million people.

00:28:55.305 --> 00:28:56.193 align:middle line:90%
So they came out.

00:28:56.193 --> 00:28:57.610 align:middle line:84%
And they went to
Tiananmen Square,

00:28:57.610 --> 00:28:58.480 align:middle line:90%
and they held up banners.

00:28:58.480 --> 00:28:59.397 align:middle line:90%
And it's all peaceful.

00:28:59.397 --> 00:29:01.450 align:middle line:90%
It's saying, Falun Dafa is good.

00:29:01.450 --> 00:29:04.750 align:middle line:84%
Because to them, all right,
this practice, many of them

00:29:04.750 --> 00:29:06.880 align:middle line:84%
believed saved their
lives or made themselves

00:29:06.880 --> 00:29:08.290 align:middle line:90%
a better person.

00:29:08.290 --> 00:29:10.210 align:middle line:84%
Why are you
persecuting a practice

00:29:10.210 --> 00:29:11.320 align:middle line:90%
that makes people better?

00:29:11.320 --> 00:29:12.403 align:middle line:90%
So they didn't understand.

00:29:12.403 --> 00:29:14.230 align:middle line:84%
So they wanted to speak
out for Falun Gong

00:29:14.230 --> 00:29:17.360 align:middle line:84%
and clarify the truth about
what is really happening.

00:29:17.360 --> 00:29:20.080 align:middle line:84%
So they went to Tiananmen, even
people from outside of China,

00:29:20.080 --> 00:29:22.550 align:middle line:84%
like people from America,
from South America,

00:29:22.550 --> 00:29:25.750 align:middle line:84%
they went to Tiananmen, and
they held up banners saying,

00:29:25.750 --> 00:29:27.400 align:middle line:90%
Falun Dafa is good.

00:29:27.400 --> 00:29:30.740 align:middle line:10%
And they were, of course,
arrested right away.

00:29:30.740 --> 00:29:34.000 align:middle line:10%
And when you are
arrested, the only thing

00:29:34.000 --> 00:29:35.710 align:middle line:10%
you need to do to
get out of prison

00:29:35.710 --> 00:29:39.880 align:middle line:10%
is to sign a promise
contract that I'm never going

00:29:39.880 --> 00:29:41.290 align:middle line:10%
to practice Falun Gong again.

00:29:41.290 --> 00:29:42.090 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:29:42.090 --> 00:29:43.307 align:middle line:90%
That's all you have to do.

00:29:43.307 --> 00:29:45.640 align:middle line:84%
And then some people are like,
well, why don't they just

00:29:45.640 --> 00:29:47.223 align:middle line:84%
sign it and just go
home and practice?

00:29:47.223 --> 00:29:51.528 align:middle line:84%
Well, I mean, to people who
100% believe that this is right,

00:29:51.528 --> 00:29:53.570 align:middle line:84%
this is not something that
should be persecuted--

00:29:53.570 --> 00:29:54.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It feels like they'd
be betraying themselves, yeah.

00:29:54.910 --> 00:29:56.760 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Exactly.

00:29:56.760 --> 00:29:58.310 align:middle line:90%
And they don't want to do that.

00:29:58.310 --> 00:30:01.120 align:middle line:84%
So that's why-- when
you don't do that,

00:30:01.120 --> 00:30:05.530 align:middle line:84%
there's all sorts of systematic
torture used on you to convince

00:30:05.530 --> 00:30:06.820 align:middle line:90%
you otherwise.

00:30:06.820 --> 00:30:09.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You mean after
they've already arrested you?

00:30:09.070 --> 00:30:09.490 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yes.

00:30:09.490 --> 00:30:10.540 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Then they
tortured them--

00:30:10.540 --> 00:30:11.290 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: They tortured them.

00:30:11.290 --> 00:30:12.400 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: To get them
to sign this document?

00:30:12.400 --> 00:30:13.712 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Exactly.

00:30:13.712 --> 00:30:14.545 align:middle line:90%
This is not made up.

00:30:14.545 --> 00:30:16.170 align:middle line:84%
This Is actually real
documented stuff.

00:30:16.170 --> 00:30:17.072 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:30:17.072 --> 00:30:18.780 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: There's things
called labor camps

00:30:18.780 --> 00:30:22.500 align:middle line:84%
in China, where you literally
are making Christmas

00:30:22.500 --> 00:30:24.820 align:middle line:90%
ornaments for no money.

00:30:24.820 --> 00:30:26.070 align:middle line:90%
And you're just doing that.

00:30:26.070 --> 00:30:26.760 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Seriously?

00:30:26.760 --> 00:30:27.240 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Oh, for sure.

00:30:27.240 --> 00:30:28.650 align:middle line:90%
There was even a crazy story.

00:30:28.650 --> 00:30:30.210 align:middle line:84%
I think there was
a couple in Canada.

00:30:30.210 --> 00:30:33.630 align:middle line:84%
They found a letter in a Teddy
Bear or a Christmas ornament.

00:30:33.630 --> 00:30:35.180 align:middle line:90%
I forgot what they bought.

00:30:35.180 --> 00:30:37.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh,
saying where they--

00:30:37.110 --> 00:30:38.243 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: It was from
a prisoner inside one

00:30:38.243 --> 00:30:39.990 align:middle line:84%
of these labor camps saying,
I'm a Falun Gong practitioner.

00:30:39.990 --> 00:30:42.430 align:middle line:84%
I'm being persecuted every
day making this stuff.

00:30:42.430 --> 00:30:44.490 align:middle line:90%
Please help me.

00:30:44.490 --> 00:30:45.990 align:middle line:84%
And then finally
it got to the point

00:30:45.990 --> 00:30:52.680 align:middle line:84%
where people realized that China
has become the number one organ

00:30:52.680 --> 00:30:54.340 align:middle line:84%
destination for people
who need organs.

00:30:54.340 --> 00:30:55.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Want to buy organs.

00:30:55.350 --> 00:30:56.558 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: And the funny thing--

00:30:56.558 --> 00:30:58.710 align:middle line:84%
not funny, but the crazy
thing-- is in China,

00:30:58.710 --> 00:31:01.257 align:middle line:84%
there's no organ
donation process.

00:31:01.257 --> 00:31:03.840 align:middle line:84%
There's not a driver's license
you sign on the back that says,

00:31:03.840 --> 00:31:05.040 align:middle line:90%
I'm willing to give my organs.

00:31:05.040 --> 00:31:05.880 align:middle line:90%
Doesn't happen.

00:31:05.880 --> 00:31:07.890 align:middle line:84%
And also Chinese
culture, we believe--

00:31:07.890 --> 00:31:10.525 align:middle line:84%
we want to be with
entire body after we die.

00:31:10.525 --> 00:31:11.400 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Well, yeah.

00:31:11.400 --> 00:31:13.700 align:middle line:84%
Your organs have
their own life force

00:31:13.700 --> 00:31:15.310 align:middle line:90%
and their own intelligence.

00:31:15.310 --> 00:31:16.110 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Right.

00:31:16.110 --> 00:31:17.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean,
which they do, which

00:31:17.460 --> 00:31:19.440 align:middle line:84%
makes the whole thing
interesting in another way.

00:31:19.440 --> 00:31:20.240 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Right.

00:31:20.240 --> 00:31:22.950 align:middle line:84%
So then China came
out and admitted

00:31:22.950 --> 00:31:26.310 align:middle line:84%
that, OK, we do execute
prisoners and take

00:31:26.310 --> 00:31:27.450 align:middle line:90%
their organs.

00:31:27.450 --> 00:31:29.290 align:middle line:90%
But who are these prisoners?

00:31:29.290 --> 00:31:30.090 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:31:30.090 --> 00:31:33.570 align:middle line:84%
So Reporters Without Borders,
all these organizations,

00:31:33.570 --> 00:31:38.123 align:middle line:84%
they went in and
started investigating.

00:31:38.123 --> 00:31:39.540 align:middle line:84%
And they realized,
OK, well you're

00:31:39.540 --> 00:31:41.490 align:middle line:84%
not going to take an
organ from an alcoholic.

00:31:41.490 --> 00:31:44.070 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to take an
organ from somebody who's sick

00:31:44.070 --> 00:31:44.920 align:middle line:90%
or whatever.

00:31:44.920 --> 00:31:45.720 align:middle line:90%
Oh, who's healthy?

00:31:45.720 --> 00:31:47.970 align:middle line:84%
Falun Gong practitioners
are really healthy.

00:31:47.970 --> 00:31:51.450 align:middle line:84%
So when you go into these
labor camps, these prisons,

00:31:51.450 --> 00:31:53.540 align:middle line:90%
your blood is tested.

00:31:53.540 --> 00:31:56.670 align:middle line:84%
And then when there's a
match, you're executed.

00:31:56.670 --> 00:31:58.260 align:middle line:90%
Maybe you're not a murderer.

00:31:58.260 --> 00:32:01.157 align:middle line:84%
But you're what they call
a prisoner of conscience,

00:32:01.157 --> 00:32:03.240 align:middle line:84%
which means that you're a
Falun Gong practitioner.

00:32:03.240 --> 00:32:04.115 align:middle line:90%
Maybe you're Tibetan.

00:32:04.115 --> 00:32:06.330 align:middle line:84%
Maybe you're House
Christian, whatever.

00:32:06.330 --> 00:32:07.360 align:middle line:90%
You're executed.

00:32:07.360 --> 00:32:08.510 align:middle line:90%
Your organs are taken.

00:32:08.510 --> 00:32:11.220 align:middle line:84%
And there was even a recorded
conversation with one

00:32:11.220 --> 00:32:14.850 align:middle line:84%
of these doctors, because one
of these reporting organizations

00:32:14.850 --> 00:32:19.560 align:middle line:84%
posed as someone
who needed an organ.

00:32:19.560 --> 00:32:20.760 align:middle line:90%
And they contacted him.

00:32:20.760 --> 00:32:22.570 align:middle line:84%
And they asked him,
OK, I need an organ.

00:32:22.570 --> 00:32:23.370 align:middle line:90%
Do you have it?

00:32:23.370 --> 00:32:23.690 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:32:23.690 --> 00:32:25.260 align:middle line:84%
OK, I need it from a
Falun Gong practitioner

00:32:25.260 --> 00:32:26.250 align:middle line:84%
because I heard they
were really healthy.

00:32:26.250 --> 00:32:26.670 align:middle line:90%
Do you have it?

00:32:26.670 --> 00:32:27.720 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:32:27.720 --> 00:32:32.497 align:middle line:84%
It's this crazy
monstrosity of a thing

00:32:32.497 --> 00:32:33.580 align:middle line:90%
that's happening in China.

00:32:33.580 --> 00:32:35.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean, it's
so sick that no one wants

00:32:35.130 --> 00:32:37.500 align:middle line:84%
to talk about it, which is
why you're asking about it.

00:32:37.500 --> 00:32:37.830 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: And nobody does.

00:32:37.830 --> 00:32:38.630 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:32:38.630 --> 00:32:42.113 align:middle line:84%
And then it came to realize,
OK, well the Bodies Exhibit,

00:32:42.113 --> 00:32:43.530 align:middle line:84%
where are they
getting the bodies?

00:32:43.530 --> 00:32:45.970 align:middle line:84%
They're getting them from
China where the bodies are.

00:32:45.970 --> 00:32:47.420 align:middle line:84%
So it came to
realize, OK, there's

00:32:47.420 --> 00:32:50.430 align:middle line:84%
a lot of bodies who are being
sold that were Falun Gong

00:32:50.430 --> 00:32:51.460 align:middle line:90%
practitioners' bodies.

00:32:51.460 --> 00:32:54.990 align:middle line:84%
Basically, it's an
enterprise profiting off

00:32:54.990 --> 00:32:58.300 align:middle line:84%
people's suffering and death
and is run by the government.

00:32:58.300 --> 00:32:59.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:32:59.100 --> 00:33:00.120 align:middle line:90%
That's sick.

00:33:00.120 --> 00:33:01.350 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yeah.

00:33:01.350 --> 00:33:02.780 align:middle line:90%
To say the least.

00:33:02.780 --> 00:33:08.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, so has it
dampened the enthusiasm

00:33:08.550 --> 00:33:10.320 align:middle line:90%
of Falun Gong in China?

00:33:10.320 --> 00:33:12.000 align:middle line:84%
Has it been driven
more underground?

00:33:12.000 --> 00:33:13.500 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: It's
definitely-- you're not

00:33:13.500 --> 00:33:15.210 align:middle line:84%
going to practice in
public, obviously.

00:33:15.210 --> 00:33:15.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, surely.

00:33:15.900 --> 00:33:18.442 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: But people in China who
are Falun Gong practitioners,

00:33:18.442 --> 00:33:21.240 align:middle line:84%
they still do their best to tell
everyone they can about, hey,

00:33:21.240 --> 00:33:22.440 align:middle line:90%
don't misunderstand us.

00:33:22.440 --> 00:33:23.430 align:middle line:90%
We're not crazy.

00:33:23.430 --> 00:33:24.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:33:24.330 --> 00:33:25.910 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: This is a good practice.

00:33:25.910 --> 00:33:28.285 align:middle line:84%
And the same thing for Falun
Gong practitioners overseas.

00:33:28.285 --> 00:33:29.420 align:middle line:90%
We do the same thing.

00:33:29.420 --> 00:33:30.220 align:middle line:90%
We talk about it.

00:33:30.220 --> 00:33:31.350 align:middle line:90%
I talk about it on my show.

00:33:31.350 --> 00:33:32.970 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, hey, look.

00:33:32.970 --> 00:33:33.960 align:middle line:90%
This is happening.

00:33:33.960 --> 00:33:36.090 align:middle line:84%
People need to be
more aware of it.

00:33:36.090 --> 00:33:39.270 align:middle line:84%
And I've tried to dispel all the
rumors from the 50 Cent Army,

00:33:39.270 --> 00:33:40.913 align:middle line:90%
saying, oh, hey.

00:33:40.913 --> 00:33:41.830 align:middle line:90%
Because I can do that.

00:33:41.830 --> 00:33:45.988 align:middle line:84%
A lot of times when they say,
oh, Falun Gong practitioners,

00:33:45.988 --> 00:33:48.030 align:middle line:84%
you're in this parade
because they're paying you.

00:33:48.030 --> 00:33:52.250 align:middle line:84%
Oh, how much did the Falun Gong
pay you to join this activity?

00:33:52.250 --> 00:33:53.550 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:33:53.550 --> 00:33:55.170 align:middle line:84%
People know what
I do for a living.

00:33:55.170 --> 00:33:56.620 align:middle line:90%
I don't get paid by anybody.

00:33:56.620 --> 00:33:59.460 align:middle line:84%
I do everything because
I want to do it.

00:33:59.460 --> 00:34:00.920 align:middle line:90%
And nobody is getting paid.

00:34:00.920 --> 00:34:04.140 align:middle line:84%
We're here talking
about the atrocities

00:34:04.140 --> 00:34:07.120 align:middle line:84%
because they are atrocities
and we want to change.

00:34:07.120 --> 00:34:09.328 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: There needs to be
more awareness around it.

00:34:09.328 --> 00:34:10.328 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yes, absolutely.

00:34:10.328 --> 00:34:12.630 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean, if there's
global pressure to stop

00:34:12.630 --> 00:34:13.980 align:middle line:90%
the practice--

00:34:13.980 --> 00:34:14.989 align:middle line:90%
this is huge.

00:34:14.989 --> 00:34:17.384 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: Well, I mean,
globally, this practice

00:34:17.384 --> 00:34:20.394 align:middle line:84%
is embraced by every single
country except China.

00:34:20.394 --> 00:34:23.002 align:middle line:90%


00:34:23.002 --> 00:34:24.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, I
was talking about

00:34:24.460 --> 00:34:29.290 align:middle line:84%
to stop the practice of
executing prisoners for organs.

00:34:29.290 --> 00:34:31.199 align:middle line:84%
I think knowledge
does have some power.

00:34:31.199 --> 00:34:33.000 align:middle line:10%
I mean, human rights groups--

00:34:33.000 --> 00:34:35.730 align:middle line:10%
activists-- can certainly
apply some kind of pressure

00:34:35.730 --> 00:34:36.770 align:middle line:10%
to the government.

00:34:36.770 --> 00:34:37.570 align:middle line:10%
I don't know.

00:34:37.570 --> 00:34:39.330 align:middle line:10%
I mean, can they be
humiliated enough

00:34:39.330 --> 00:34:42.060 align:middle line:10%
to stop it if it's
in their thinking

00:34:42.060 --> 00:34:43.762 align:middle line:10%
if they're profiting from it?

00:34:43.762 --> 00:34:45.429 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: I mean, China
is its own animal.

00:34:45.429 --> 00:34:45.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, I know.

00:34:45.840 --> 00:34:46.580 align:middle line:90%
That's what I'm wondering.

00:34:46.580 --> 00:34:47.984 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Everything is shut off.

00:34:47.984 --> 00:34:48.699 align:middle line:84%
Like, information
can't reach China.

00:34:48.699 --> 00:34:50.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --from the
rest of the world.

00:34:50.100 --> 00:34:51.058 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Right, exactly.

00:34:51.058 --> 00:34:52.380 align:middle line:90%
That's a little tougher.

00:34:52.380 --> 00:34:54.752 align:middle line:84%
But like you said, awareness
was really the only way.

00:34:54.752 --> 00:34:55.710 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, right.

00:34:55.710 --> 00:34:56.199 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: So more people know.

00:34:56.199 --> 00:34:57.720 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, it's very
brave of you to talk about it,

00:34:57.720 --> 00:34:59.280 align:middle line:90%
because it's really very harsh.

00:34:59.280 --> 00:35:01.890 align:middle line:90%
It's really painful and sad.

00:35:01.890 --> 00:35:04.950 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: Well, if
I'm putting myself

00:35:04.950 --> 00:35:07.710 align:middle line:84%
in the position of somebody over
there who my only crime was I

00:35:07.710 --> 00:35:10.408 align:middle line:84%
did a meditation exercise
to help me become a better

00:35:10.408 --> 00:35:12.700 align:middle line:84%
person and healthier person,
and I was thrown in prison

00:35:12.700 --> 00:35:16.810 align:middle line:84%
and tortured for it, I want to
help those people who are still

00:35:16.810 --> 00:35:17.610 align:middle line:90%
being tortured.

00:35:17.610 --> 00:35:18.600 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:35:18.600 --> 00:35:19.892 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: I want to get them out.

00:35:19.892 --> 00:35:21.030 align:middle line:90%
I want this to stop.

00:35:21.030 --> 00:35:23.095 align:middle line:84%
I want something that
has benefited my family

00:35:23.095 --> 00:35:24.720 align:middle line:84%
so much-- my mom
wouldn't be here today

00:35:24.720 --> 00:35:25.637 align:middle line:90%
if it wasn't for this.

00:35:25.637 --> 00:35:28.080 align:middle line:84%
My dad would still be
screaming at something.

00:35:28.080 --> 00:35:29.065 align:middle line:90%
So I want to help.

00:35:29.065 --> 00:35:31.440 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I love that you're
doing that, as uncomfortable

00:35:31.440 --> 00:35:33.690 align:middle line:84%
as it is and why we chose
to do that today as well.

00:35:33.690 --> 00:35:36.330 align:middle line:84%
So now you have quite
a number of people

00:35:36.330 --> 00:35:38.580 align:middle line:84%
that have learned about this
that didn't already know.

00:35:38.580 --> 00:35:39.330 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: I appreciate that.

00:35:39.330 --> 00:35:41.122 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And now so
what about Falun Gong,

00:35:41.122 --> 00:35:44.610 align:middle line:84%
in terms of its own growth
in America and other places.

00:35:44.610 --> 00:35:46.830 align:middle line:84%
I know it's relatively
little known.

00:35:46.830 --> 00:35:47.850 align:middle line:90%
But is it growing?

00:35:47.850 --> 00:35:48.690 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Yeah.

