00:58:34.730 --> 00:58:37.363 align:middle line:84%
And I think if you lose
that, I mean, that's it.

00:58:37.363 --> 00:58:38.530 align:middle line:90%
That's-- everything is gone.

00:58:38.530 --> 00:58:39.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:58:39.330 --> 00:58:41.270 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEN: So I'm moving,
actually, from New York

00:58:41.270 --> 00:58:42.860 align:middle line:84%
City in a couple of
months to Seattle,

00:58:42.860 --> 00:58:45.130 align:middle line:90%
just a little peace and quiet.

00:58:45.130 --> 00:58:46.380 align:middle line:90%
I love the Pacific Northwest.

00:58:46.380 --> 00:58:47.060 align:middle line:90%
I love rain.

00:58:47.060 --> 00:58:48.020 align:middle line:90%
A lot of people don't get that.

00:58:48.020 --> 00:58:48.820 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:58:48.820 --> 00:58:50.330 align:middle line:90%
Cozy rain, some nice soup.

00:58:50.330 --> 00:58:50.930 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I like it, too.

00:58:50.930 --> 00:58:51.390 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: Disney movie.

00:58:51.390 --> 00:58:53.190 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: When you're in sun
all the time in California--

00:58:53.190 --> 00:58:55.882 align:middle line:84%
I've been there, Arizona and
California, my whole life--

00:58:55.882 --> 00:58:56.840 align:middle line:90%
you like a little rain.

00:58:56.840 --> 00:58:57.820 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEN: I love rain.

00:58:57.820 --> 00:58:59.500 align:middle line:84%
And you know, like
I said, pair that up

00:58:59.500 --> 00:59:02.630 align:middle line:84%
